{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897101802,"sessionID":"ses_284491adcffeLHpQLAseZVZ6d5","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb741860015sbH388AdYOuoP","messageID":"msg_d7bb7260f001EEonoUn4YYImRr","sessionID":"ses_284491adcffeLHpQLAseZVZ6d5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018 Design: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-018  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/agentd`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S (Small)\n9: \n10: The Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller is a Kubernetes controller that automatically deletes AgentRuntime resources that have exceeded their configured idle timeout. It monitors the `LastActivityTime` field in AgentRuntime status and compares it against the `IdleTimeoutSeconds` specified in the spec to determine when a resource should be cleaned up.\n11: \n12: This implementation integrates with:\n13: - **AgentRuntime API (pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1)**: Watches AgentRuntime resources\n14: - **client-go library**: Uses generated Kubernetes clientset for API interactions\n15: - **controller-runtime**: Manages the controller lifecycle and reconciliation loop\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Architecture\n20: \n21: ### High-Level Design\n22: \n23: ```\n24: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n25: │                         Kubernetes Cluster                                   │\n26: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n27: │  │                         AgentRuntime Resources                          │  │\n28: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐                    │  │\n29: │  │  │  Runtime 1  │  │  Runtime 2  │  │  Runtime N  │                    │  │\n30: │  │  │ (active)    │  │ (idle 20m)  │  │ (idle 45m)  │                    │  │\n31: │  │  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘                    │  │\n32: │  │         │                │                │                            │  │\n33: │  │         │                ▼                ▼                            │  │\n34: │  │         │         ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐                  │  │\n35: │  │         │         │ Timeout: 15m │  │ Timeout: 30m │                  │  │\n36: │  │         │         │ DELETE       │  │ DELETE       │                  │  │\n37: │  │         │         └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘                  │  │\n38: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n39: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n40: │                      Agentd Controller (Idle Cleanup)                        │\n41: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n42: │  │                      Reconciliation Loop                                │  │\n43: │  │  ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌───────────┐  │  │\n44: │  │  │    Get      │──►│   Check     │──►│  Calculate  │──►│  Delete   │  │  │\n45: │  │  │   AgentRun  │   │ IdleTimeout │   │  Remaining  │   │  if Idle  │  │  │\n46: │  │  │   time      │   │   Config    │   │   Time      │   │  Timeout  │  │  │\n47: │  │  └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └───────────┘  │  │\n48: │  │         │                │                │                │          │  │\n49: │  │         ▼                ▼                ▼                ▼          │  │\n50: │  │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n51: │  │  │                    Requeue Decision                              │  │  │\n52: │  │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐              │  │  │\n53: │  │  │  │  No Timeout │  │   Idle      │  │   Error     │              │  │  │\n54: │  │  │  │  Configured │  │   Detected  │  │   Occurred  │              │  │  │\n55: │  │  │  │  ──► Skip   │  │  ──► Delete │  │  ──► Requeue│              │  │  │\n56: │  │  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘              │  │  │\n57: │  │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n58: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n59: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n60: │                      Client-Go Integration Layer                             │\n61: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │\n62: │  │  AgentRuntime    │  │  Typed Client    │  │  Status Subresource      │   │\n63: │  │  Interface       │  │  (v1alpha1)      │  │  (Get/Update)            │   │\n64: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │\n65: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n66: ```\n67: \n68: ### Component Architecture\n69: \n70: ```\n71: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n72: │                     Idle Cleanup Controller Flow                             │\n73: │                                                                              │\n74: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n75: │  │  Watch   │──►│  Reconcile│──►│   Get    │──►│  Parse   │──►│  Check   │  │\n76: │  │  Events  │   │  Request  │   │  AgentRun │   │  Timeout │   │  Activity│  │\n77: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   │  time     │   │  Config  │   │  Time    │  │\n78: │                                └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘  │\n79: │                                                                     │        │\n80: │                          ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┘        │\n81: │                          │                                                   │\n82: │                          ▼                                                   │\n83: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n84: │  │  Return  │◀──│  Schedule│◀──│  Delete  │◀──│  Expired │◀──│Calculate │  │\n85: │  │  Result  │   │  Requeue │   │  Resource│   │  ?       │   │Idle Time │  │\n86: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘  │\n87: │                                                                              │\n88: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n89: ```\n90: \n91: ### Component Interactions\n92: \n93: | Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n94: |-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n95: | **Reconciler** | Core reconciliation logic for AgentRuntime | context.Context, reconcile.Request | reconcile.Result, error |\n96: | **AgentRuntimeInterface** | Typed client for AgentRuntime CRUD | AgentRuntime objects | AgentRuntime operations |\n97: | **IdleTimeoutChecker** | Determines if resource has exceeded idle timeout | AgentRuntime status | bool (expired), time.Duration (remaining) |\n98: | **CleanupExecutor** | Performs the deletion of expired resources | AgentRuntime reference | error |\n99: | **RequeueCalculator** | Calculates next requeue time | remaining duration | reconcile.Result |\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## Directory Structure\n104: \n105: ```\n106: pkg/agentd/\n107: ├── controller.go         # Main reconciler implementation (~180 lines)\n108: ├── controller_test.go    # Unit tests for reconciler (~200 lines)\n109: ├── config.go             # Controller configuration (~80 lines)\n110: ├── metrics.go            # Prometheus metrics for cleanup operations (~60 lines)\n111: └── doc.go                # Package documentation (~20 lines)\n112: \n113: cmd/agentd/\n114: └── main.go               # Controller entry point (~100 lines)\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ## Data Structures\n120: \n121: ### Domain Types\n122: \n123: #### Reconciler\n124: \n125: ```go\n126: // Reconciler reconciles AgentRuntime objects for idle cleanup.\n127: type Reconciler struct {\n128:     // Client is the Kubernetes client for AgentRuntime resources\n129:     client client.Client\n130:     \n131:     // Scheme is the runtime scheme for type registration\n132:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n133:     \n134:     // Clock provides time functionality (allows mocking in tests)\n135:     Clock Clock\n136:     \n137:     // Metrics collects operational metrics\n138:     Metrics *Metrics\n139: }\n140: \n141: // Clock abstracts time operations for testability.\n142: type Clock interface {\n143:     Now() time.Time\n144: }\n145: \n146: // realClock implements Clock using the system clock.\n147: type realClock struct{}\n148: \n149: func (c *realClock) Now() time.Time {\n150:     return time.Now()\n151: }\n152: \n153: // NewReconciler creates a new AgentRuntime idle cleanup reconciler.\n154: func NewReconciler(client client.Client, scheme *runtime.Scheme) *Reconciler {\n155:     return &Reconciler{\n156:         Client:  client,\n157:         Scheme:  scheme,\n158:         Clock:   &realClock{},\n159:         Metrics: newMetrics(),\n160:     }\n161: }\n162: ```\n163: \n164: #### IdleTimeoutConfig\n165: \n166: ```go\n167: // IdleTimeoutConfig holds the idle timeout configuration.\n168: type IdleTimeoutConfig struct {\n169:     // DefaultTimeout is the fallback timeout when not specified in spec\n170:     DefaultTimeout time.Duration\n171:     \n172:     // MaxTimeout is the maximum allowed idle timeout\n173:     MaxTimeout time.Duration\n174:     \n175:     // MinTimeout is the minimum allowed idle timeout\n176:     MinTimeout time.Duration\n177: }\n178: \n179: // DefaultIdleTimeoutConfig returns the default configuration.\n180: func DefaultIdleTimeoutConfig() IdleTimeoutConfig {\n181:     return IdleTimeoutConfig{\n182:         DefaultTimeout: 15 * time.Minute,\n183:         MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n184:         MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n185:     }\n186: }\n187: \n188: // Validate checks if the configuration is valid.\n189: func (c *IdleTimeoutConfig) Validate() error {\n190:     if c.DefaultTimeout < c.MinTimeout {\n191:         return fmt.Errorf(\"default timeout %v is less than minimum %v\", \n192:             c.DefaultTimeout, c.MinTimeout)\n193:     }\n194:     if c.DefaultTimeout > c.MaxTimeout {\n195:         return fmt.Errorf(\"default timeout %v is greater than maximum %v\",\n196:             c.DefaultTimeout, c.MaxTimeout)\n197:     }\n198:     return nil\n199: }\n200: ```\n201: \n202: #### CleanupResult\n203: \n204: ```go\n205: // CleanupResult represents the outcome of a cleanup check.\n206: type CleanupResult struct {\n207:     // ShouldDelete indicates whether the resource should be deleted\n208:     ShouldDelete bool\n209:     \n210:     // Reason provides a human-readable explanation\n211:     Reason string\n212:     \n213:     // IdleDuration is how long the resource has been idle\n214:     IdleDuration time.Duration\n215:     \n216:     // TimeoutDuration is the configured timeout\n217:     TimeoutDuration time.Duration\n218:     \n219:     // RemainingTime is time until cleanup (zero if ShouldDelete)\n220:     RemainingTime time.Duration\n221: }\n222: \n223: // String returns a string representation of the result.\n224: func (r *CleanupResult) String() string {\n225:     if r.ShouldDelete {\n226:         return fmt.Sprintf(\"cleanup: %s (idle %v, timeout %v)\", \n227:             r.Reason, r.IdleDuration, r.TimeoutDuration)\n228:     }\n229:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"skip: %s (idle %v, remaining %v)\",\n230:         r.Reason, r.IdleDuration, r.RemainingTime)\n231: }\n232: ```\n233: \n234: ### Request/Response Types\n235: \n236: #### ReconcileRequest (Internal)\n237: \n238: ```go\n239: // ReconcileRequest wraps controller-runtime's reconcile.Request.\n240: type ReconcileRequest struct {\n241:     // NamespacedName identifies the AgentRuntime resource\n242:     NamespacedName types.NamespacedName\n243: }\n244: \n245: // ToControllerRuntime converts to controller-runtime request.\n246: func (r *ReconcileRequest) ToControllerRuntime() reconcile.Request {\n247:     return reconcile.Request{NamespacedName: r.NamespacedName}\n248: }\n249: ```\n250: \n251: ### Internal Types\n252: \n253: #### ControllerConfig\n254: \n255: ```go\n256: // ControllerConfig contains environment-based configuration.\n257: type ControllerConfig struct {\n258:     // LeaderElection enables leader election for HA\n259:     LeaderElection bool\n260:     \n261:     // SyncPeriod is the period for full re-listing of resources\n262:     SyncPeriod time.Duration\n263:     \n264:     // WorkerCount is the number of concurrent reconcile workers\n265:     WorkerCount int\n266:     \n267:     // IdleTimeout is the default idle timeout configuration\n268:     IdleTimeout IdleTimeoutConfig\n269:     \n270:     // MetricsBindAddress is the address for metrics server (\":8080\" or \"0\" to disable)\n271:     MetricsBindAddress string\n272:     \n273:     // HealthProbeBindAddress is the address for health probes (\":8081\" or \"0\" to disable)\n274:     HealthProbeBindAddress string\n275: }\n276: \n277: // LoadConfig loads configuration from environment variables.\n278: func LoadConfig() (*ControllerConfig, error) {\n279:     cfg := &ControllerConfig{\n280:         LeaderElection:         getEnvBool(\"AGENTD_LEADER_ELECTION\", true),\n281:         SyncPeriod:             getEnvDuration(\"AGENTD_SYNC_PERIOD\", 10*time.Minute),\n282:         WorkerCount:            getEnvInt(\"AGENTD_WORKER_COUNT\", 1),\n283:         IdleTimeout:            DefaultIdleTimeoutConfig(),\n284:         MetricsBindAddress:     getEnvOrDefault(\"AGENTD_METRICS_BIND_ADDRESS\", \"0\"),\n285:         HealthProbeBindAddress: getEnvOrDefault(\"AGENTD_HEALTH_PROBE_BIND_ADDRESS\", \"0\"),\n286:     }\n287:     \n288:     // Override idle timeout from env if specified\n289:     if timeout := os.Getenv(\"AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT\"); timeout != \"\" {\n290:         if d, err := time.ParseDuration(timeout); err == nil {\n291:             cfg.IdleTimeout.DefaultTimeout = d\n292:         } else {\n293:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"invalid AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT: %v\", err)\n294:         }\n295:     }\n296:     \n297:     if err := cfg.IdleTimeout.Validate(); err != nil {\n298:         return nil, err\n299:     }\n300:     \n301:     return cfg, nil\n302: }\n303: ```\n304: \n305: #### Metrics\n306: \n307: ```go\n308: // Metrics holds Prometheus metrics for the controller.\n309: type Metrics struct {\n310:     // ReconcileTotal is the total number of reconciliations\n311:     ReconcileTotal prometheus.Counter\n312:     \n313:     // ReconcileErrors is the total number of reconciliation errors\n314:     ReconcileErrors prometheus.Counter\n315:     \n316:     // CleanupTotal is the total number of successful cleanups\n317:     CleanupTotal prometheus.Counter\n318:     \n319:     // CleanupDuration is the duration of cleanup operations\n320:     CleanupDuration prometheus.Histogram\n321:     \n322:     // IdleDuration is the idle duration of cleaned resources\n323:     IdleDuration prometheus.Histogram\n324: }\n325: \n326: // newMetrics creates a new Metrics instance.\n327: func newMetrics() *Metrics {\n328:     return &Metrics{\n329:         ReconcileTotal: prometheus.NewCounter(prometheus.CounterOpts{\n330:             Name: \"agentd_idle_cleanup_reconcile_total\",\n331:             Help: \"Total number of idle cleanup reconciliations\",\n332:         }),\n333:         ReconcileErrors: prometheus.NewCounter(prometheus.CounterOpts{\n334:             Name: \"agentd_idle_cleanup_reconcile_errors_total\",\n335:             Help: \"Total number of idle cleanup reconciliation errors\",\n336:         }),\n337:         CleanupTotal: prometheus.NewCounter(prometheus.CounterOpts{\n338:             Name: \"agentd_idle_cleanup_total\",\n339:             Help: \"Total number of idle cleanups performed\",\n340:         }),\n341:         CleanupDuration: prometheus.NewHistogram(prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n342:             Name:    \"agentd_idle_cleanup_duration_seconds\",\n343:             Help:    \"Duration of idle cleanup operations\",\n344:             Buckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n345:         }),\n346:         IdleDuration: prometheus.NewHistogram(prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n347:             Name:    \"agentd_idle_cleanup_idle_duration_seconds\",\n348:             Help:    \"Idle duration of cleaned resources\",\n349:             Buckets: []float64{60, 300, 600, 1800, 3600, 7200, 86400},\n350:         }),\n351:     }\n352: }\n353: \n354: // Register registers metrics with the provided registry.\n355: func (m *Metrics) Register(reg prometheus.Registerer) error {\n356:     collectors := []prometheus.Collector{\n357:         m.ReconcileTotal,\n358:         m.ReconcileErrors,\n359:         m.CleanupTotal,\n360:         m.CleanupDuration,\n361:         m.IdleDuration,\n362:     }\n363:     for _, c := range collectors {\n364:         if err := reg.Register(c); err != nil {\n365:             return err\n366:         }\n367:     }\n368:     return nil\n369: }\n370: ```\n371: \n372: ### Constants\n373: \n374: ```go\n375: // Default configuration values\n376: const (\n377:     // DefaultIdleTimeout is the default idle timeout when not specified\n378:     DefaultIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n379:     \n380:     // DefaultRequeueInterval is the default interval for requeuing when error occurs\n381:     DefaultRequeueInterval = 30 * time.Second\n382:     \n383:     // MinRequeueInterval is the minimum requeue interval\n384:     MinRequeueInterval = 5 * time.Second\n385: )\n386: \n387: // Error reasons for status updates\n388: const (\n389:     // ReasonIdleTimeout indicates cleanup due to idle timeout\n390:     ReasonIdleTimeout = \"IdleTimeoutExceeded\"\n391:     \n392:     // ReasonNoIdleConfig indicates no idle timeout configured\n393:     ReasonNoIdleConfig = \"NoIdleTimeoutConfigured\"\n394:     \n395:     // ReasonActive indicates resource is still active\n396:     ReasonActive = \"ResourceStillActive\"\n397: )\n398: \n399: // Event types\n400: const (\n401:     // EventTypeNormal indicates a normal event\n402:     EventTypeNormal = \"Normal\"\n403:     \n404:     // EventTypeWarning indicates a warning event\n405:     EventTypeWarning = \"Warning\"\n406: )\n407: \n408: // Event reasons\n409: const (\n410:     // EventReasonIdleCleanup indicates successful idle cleanup\n411:     EventReasonIdleCleanup = \"IdleCleanup\"\n412:     \n413:     // EventReasonCleanupFailed indicates failed cleanup\n414:     EventReasonCleanupFailed = \"CleanupFailed\"\n415: )\n416: ```\n417: \n418: ---\n419: \n420: ## API Contracts\n421: \n422: ### Reconciler Interface\n423: \n424: ```go\n425: // ReconcilerInterface defines the interface for AgentRuntime reconciliation.\n426: type ReconcilerInterface interface {\n427:     // Reconcile performs idle cleanup reconciliation for the given AgentRuntime.\n428:     //\n429:     // Parameters:\n430:     //   - ctx: Context for cancellation and timeouts\n431:     //   - req: Reconcile request containing the AgentRuntime namespaced name\n432:     //\n433:     // Returns:\n434:     //   - reconcile.Result: Indicates whether to requeue and when\n435:     //   - error: Non-nil if reconciliation failed (triggers requeue with backoff)\n436:     //\n437:     // Behavior:\n438:     //   1. Fetch AgentRuntime from Kubernetes API\n439:     //   2. Check if IdleTimeoutSeconds is configured in spec\n440:     //   3. Parse LastActivityTime from status\n441:     //   4. Calculate idle duration\n442:     //   5. If idle duration > timeout, delete the resource\n443:     //   6. Otherwise, requeue after remaining time\n444:     Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error)\n445: }\n446: \n447: // SetupWithManager sets up the reconciler with the controller manager.\n448: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n449:     return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n450:         For(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}).\n451:         WithEventFilter(predicate.GenerationChangedPredicate{}).\n452:         Complete(r)\n453: }\n454: ```\n455: \n456: ### Idle Timeout Checker\n457: \n458: ```go\n459: // CheckIdleTimeout determines if an AgentRuntime has exceeded its idle timeout.\n460: //\n461: // Parameters:\n462: //   - agentRuntime: The AgentRuntime to check\n463: //   - now: Current time\n464: //\n465: // Returns:\n466: //   - *CleanupResult: Result indicating whether cleanup should occur\n467: //   - error: If status fields cannot be parsed\n468: //\n469: // Logic:\n470: //   1. If IdleTimeoutSeconds is nil/0, return ShouldDelete=false (no timeout configured)\n471: //   2. If LastActivityTime is nil, use creation timestamp\n472: //   3. Calculate idleDuration = now - lastActivityTime\n473: //   4. timeoutDuration = IdleTimeoutSeconds converted to time.Duration\n474: //   5. If idleDuration >= timeoutDuration, return ShouldDelete=true\n475: //   6. Otherwise, return ShouldDelete=false with RemainingTime = timeoutDuration - idleDuration\n476: func CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, now time.Time) (*CleanupResult, error)\n477: ```\n478: \n479: ### Cleanup Executor\n480: \n481: ```go\n482: // ExecuteCleanup deletes an AgentRuntime that has exceeded its idle timeout.\n483: //\n484: // Parameters:\n485: //   - ctx: Context for the delete operation\n486: //   - client: Kubernetes client\n487: //   - agentRuntime: The AgentRuntime to delete\n488: //\n489: // Returns:\n490: //   - error: nil if deletion initiated successfully, otherwise error\n491: //\n492: // Notes:\n493: //   - Uses foreground deletion for graceful cleanup\n494: //   - Sets deletion reason annotation before deletion\n495: func ExecuteCleanup(ctx context.Context, client client.Client, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) error\n496: ```\n497: \n498: ### Configuration Functions\n499: \n500: ```go\n501: // LoadConfig loads controller configuration from environment variables.\n502: //\n503: // Required: None (all have defaults)\n504: //\n505: // Optional environment variables:\n506: //   - AGENTD_LEADER_ELECTION: Enable leader election (default: \"true\")\n507: //   - AGENTD_SYNC_PERIOD: Full re-list period (default: \"10m\")\n508: //   - AGENTD_WORKER_COUNT: Concurrent workers (default: \"1\")\n509: //   - AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT: Default idle timeout (default: \"15m\")\n510: //   - AGENTD_METRICS_BIND_ADDRESS: Metrics server address (default: \"0\")\n511: //   - AGENTD_HEALTH_PROBE_BIND_ADDRESS: Health probe address (default: \"0\")\n512: //\n513: // Returns:\n514: //   - *ControllerConfig: Loaded configuration\n515: //   - error: If configuration is invalid\n516: func LoadConfig() (*ControllerConfig, error)\n517: \n518: // GetTimeoutDuration extracts timeout duration from AgentRuntime spec.\n519: //\n520: // Returns:\n521: //   - time.Duration: The idle timeout duration\n522: //   - bool: true if timeout is configured, false otherwise\n523: func GetTimeoutDuration(spec *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec, defaults IdleTimeoutConfig) (time.Duration, bool)\n524: ```\n525: \n526: ### Metrics Functions\n527: \n528: ```go\n529: // RecordReconcile records a reconciliation attempt.\n530: func (m *Metrics) RecordReconcile()\n531: \n532: // RecordReconcileError records a reconciliation error.\n533: func (m *Metrics) RecordReconcileError()\n534: \n535: // RecordCleanup records a successful cleanup.\n536: func (m *Metrics) RecordCleanup(duration time.Duration, idleDuration time.Duration)\n537: ```\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## Error Handling\n542: \n543: ### Error Categories and Codes\n544: \n545: | Error | Code | Description | Retryable | Handling Strategy |\n546: |-------|------|-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n547: | `ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound` | `NOT_FOUND` | AgentRuntime was deleted | No | Return success (no requeue) |\n548: | `ErrGetAgentRuntimeFailed` | `GET_FAILED` | Failed to fetch AgentRuntime | Yes | Requeue with backoff |\n549: | `ErrParseLastActivity` | `PARSE_FAILED` | Failed to parse LastActivityTime | No | Log and skip resource |\n550: | `ErrDeleteFailed` | `DELETE_FAILED` | Deletion API call failed | Yes | Requeue with backoff |\n551: | `ErrInvalidTimeout` | `INVALID_TIMEOUT` | IdleTimeoutSeconds invalid | No | Log and skip resource |\n552: \n553: ### Sentinel Errors\n554: \n555: ```go\n556: // Controller errors\n557: var (\n558:     ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound = errors.New(\"agentruntime: resource not found\")\n559:     ErrGetAgentRuntimeFailed = errors.New(\"agentruntime: failed to get resource\")\n560:     ErrParseLastActivity = errors.New(\"agentruntime: failed to parse last activity time\")\n561:     ErrDeleteFailed = errors.New(\"agentruntime: failed to delete resource\")\n562:     ErrInvalidTimeout = errors.New(\"agentruntime: invalid idle timeout configuration\")\n563: )\n564: ```\n565: \n566: ### Error Structures\n567: \n568: ```go\n569: // ReconcileError represents a reconciliation error with context.\n570: type ReconcileError struct {\n571:     // Code is the machine-readable error code\n572:     Code string `json:\"code\"`\n573:     \n574:     // Message is the human-readable error message\n575:     Message string `json:\"message\"`\n576:     \n577:     // Resource is the namespaced name of the affected resource\n578:     Resource types.NamespacedName `json:\"resource\"`\n579:     \n580:     // Retryable indicates if the error is retryable\n581:     Retryable bool `json:\"retryable\"`\n582:     \n583:     // underlying is the wrapped error\n584:     underlying error\n585: }\n586: \n587: // Error returns the error string.\n588: func (e *ReconcileError) Error() string {\n589:     if e.underlying != nil {\n590:         return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (resource: %s): %v\", \n591:             e.Code, e.Message, e.Resource, e.underlying)\n592:     }\n593:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (resource: %s)\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Resource)\n594: }\n595: \n596: // Unwrap returns the wrapped error.\n597: func (e *ReconcileError) Unwrap() error {\n598:     return e.underlying\n599: }\n600: \n601: // IsRetryable returns true if the error is retryable.\n602: func (e *ReconcileError) IsRetryable() bool {\n603:     return e.Retryable\n604: }\n605: \n606: // NewReconcileError creates a new ReconcileError.\n607: func NewReconcileError(code, message string, resource types.NamespacedName, retryable bool, underlying error) *ReconcileError {\n608:     return &ReconcileError{\n609:         Code:       code,\n610:         Message:    message,\n611:         Resource:   resource,\n612:         Retryable:  retryable,\n613:         underlying: underlying,\n614:     }\n615: }\n616: ```\n617: \n618: ### Error Handling Patterns\n619: \n620: #### Reconcile Error Handling\n621: \n622: ```go\n623: func (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error) {\n624:     r.Metrics.RecordReconcile()\n625:     \n626:     log := log.FromContext(ctx).WithValues(\"agentruntime\", req.NamespacedName)\n627:     \n628:     // Fetch AgentRuntime\n629:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}\n630:     if err := r.client.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, agentRuntime); err != nil {\n631:         if errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n632:             log.Info(\"AgentRuntime not found, skipping\")\n633:             return reconcile.Result{}, nil\n634:         }\n635:         r.Metrics.RecordReconcileError()\n636:         return reconcile.Result{}, NewReconcileError(\n637:             \"GET_FAILED\",\n638:             \"failed to get AgentRuntime\",\n639:             req.NamespacedName,\n640:             true,\n641:             err,\n642:         )\n643:     }\n644:     \n645:     // Check idle timeout\n646:     result, err := r.checkAndCleanup(ctx, agentRuntime)\n647:     if err != nil {\n648:         r.Metrics.RecordReconcileError()\n649:         reconcileErr, ok := err.(*ReconcileError)\n650:         if ok && !reconcileErr.IsRetryable() {\n651:             log.Error(err, \"Non-retryable error during cleanup, skipping\")\n652:             return reconcile.Result{}, nil\n653:         }\n654:         return reconcile.Result{RequeueAfter: DefaultRequeueInterval}, err\n655:     }\n656:     \n657:     return result, nil\n658: }\n659: ```\n660: \n661: #### Check and Cleanup Pattern\n662: \n663: ```go\n664: func (r *Reconciler) checkAndCleanup(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (reconcile.Result, error) {\n665:     log := log.FromContext(ctx)\n666:     \n667:     // Check idle timeout\n668:     cleanupResult, err := CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime, r.Clock.Now())\n669:     if err != nil {\n670:         return reconcile.Result{}, NewReconcileError(\n671:             \"PARSE_FAILED\",\n672:             \"failed to check idle timeout\",\n673:             types.NamespacedName{Name: agentRuntime.Name, Namespace: agentRuntime.Namespace},\n674:             false,\n675:             err,\n676:         )\n677:     }\n678:     \n679:     log.V(1).Info(\"Idle check result\", \"result\", cleanupResult.String())\n680:     \n681:     // If should delete, execute cleanup\n682:     if cleanupResult.ShouldDelete {\n683:         start := r.Clock.Now()\n684:         if err := ExecuteCleanup(ctx, r.client, agentRuntime); err != nil {\n685:             return reconcile.Result{}, NewReconcileError(\n686:                 \"DELETE_FAILED\",\n687:                 \"failed to delete idle AgentRuntime\",\n688:                 types.NamespacedName{Name: agentRuntime.Name, Namespace: agentRuntime.Namespace},\n689:                 true,\n690:                 err,\n691:             )\n692:         }\n693:         \n694:         duration := r.Clock.Now().Sub(start)\n695:         r.Metrics.RecordCleanup(duration, cleanupResult.IdleDuration)\n696:         log.Info(\"Deleted idle AgentRuntime\",\n697:             \"idleDuration\", cleanupResult.IdleDuration,\n698:             \"timeoutDuration\", cleanupResult.TimeoutDuration)\n699:         \n700:         return reconcile.Result{}, nil\n701:     }\n702:     \n703:     // Requeue after remaining time\n704:     if cleanupResult.RemainingTime > 0 {\n705:         // Add small buffer to avoid race conditions\n706:         requeueAfter := cleanupResult.RemainingTime + MinRequeueInterval\n707:         log.V(1).Info(\"Requeuing for next idle check\",\n708:             \"requeueAfter\", requeueAfter,\n709:             \"remainingTime\", cleanupResult.RemainingTime)\n710:         return reconcile.Result{RequeueAfter: requeueAfter}, nil\n711:     }\n712:     \n713:     return reconcile.Result{}, nil\n714: }\n715: ```\n716: \n717: ---\n718: \n719: ## Testing Strategy\n720: \n721: ### Unit Tests\n722: \n723: #### controller_test.go\n724: \n725: ```go\n726: func TestReconciler_Reconcile_NotFound(t *testing.T) {\n727:     // Setup\n728:     client := fake.NewClientBuilder().Build()\n729:     reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n730:     \n731:     // Execute - resource doesn't exist\n732:     result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n733:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n734:     })\n735:     \n736:     // Assert\n737:     require.NoError(t, err)\n738:     assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n739:     assert.Equal(t, time.Duration(0), result.RequeueAfter)\n740: }\n741: \n742: func TestReconciler_Reconcile_NoIdleTimeout(t *testing.T) {\n743:     // Setup - AgentRuntime without idle timeout\n744:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n745:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n746:             Name:      \"test\",\n747:             Namespace: \"default\",\n748:         },\n749:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n750:             // IdleTimeoutSeconds not set\n751:         },\n752:     }\n753:     \n754:     client := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithObjects(agentRuntime).Build()\n755:     reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n756:     \n757:     // Execute\n758:     result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n759:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n760:     })\n761:     \n762:     // Assert - should not requeue, no timeout configured\n763:     require.NoError(t, err)\n764:     assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n765:     \n766:     // Verify resource still exists\n767:     err = client.Get(context.Background(), types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n768:     require.NoError(t, err)\n769: }\n770: \n771: func TestReconciler_Reconcile_IdleTimeoutNotExpired(t *testing.T) {\n772:     // Setup\n773:     now := time.Now()\n774:     lastActivity := metav1.NewTime(now.Add(-5 * time.Minute)) // 5 minutes ago\n775:     \n776:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n777:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n778:             Name:      \"test\",\n779:             Namespace: \"default\",\n780:         },\n781:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n782:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](900), // 15 minutes\n783:         },\n784:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n785:             LastActivityTime: &lastActivity,\n786:         },\n787:     }\n788:     \n789:     client := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithObjects(agentRuntime).Build()\n790:     reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n791:     reconciler.Clock = &fakeClock{now: now}\n792:     \n793:     // Execute\n794:     result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n795:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n796:     })\n797:     \n798:     // Assert - should requeue after ~10 minutes\n799:     require.NoError(t, err)\n800:     assert.InDelta(t, 10*time.Minute, result.RequeueAfter, float64(time.Minute))\n801:     \n802:     // Verify resource still exists\n803:     err = client.Get(context.Background(), types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n804:     require.NoError(t, err)\n805: }\n806: \n807: func TestReconciler_Reconcile_IdleTimeoutExpired(t *testing.T) {\n808:     // Setup\n809:     now := time.Now()\n810:     lastActivity := metav1.NewTime(now.Add(-30 * time.Minute)) // 30 minutes ago\n811:     \n812:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n813:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n814:             Name:      \"test\",\n815:             Namespace: \"default\",\n816:         },\n817:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n818:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](900), // 15 minutes\n819:         },\n820:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n821:             LastActivityTime: &lastActivity,\n822:         },\n823:     }\n824:     \n825:     client := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithObjects(agentRuntime).Build()\n826:     reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n827:     reconciler.Clock = &fakeClock{now: now}\n828:     \n829:     // Execute\n830:     result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n831:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n832:     })\n833:     \n834:     // Assert - should not requeue, resource deleted\n835:     require.NoError(t, err)\n836:     assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n837:     \n838:     // Verify resource deleted\n839:     err = client.Get(context.Background(), types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n840:     require.Error(t, err)\n841:     assert.True(t, errors.IsNotFound(err))\n842: }\n843: \n844: func TestReconciler_Reconcile_NoLastActivityTime(t *testing.T) {\n845:     // Setup - no LastActivityTime, should use creation time\n846:     now := time.Now()\n847:     creationTime := metav1.NewTime(now.Add(-20 * time.Minute))\n848:     \n849:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n850:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n851:             Name:              \"test\",\n852:             Namespace:         \"default\",\n853:             CreationTimestamp: creationTime,\n854:         },\n855:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n856:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](900), // 15 minutes\n857:         },\n858:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n859:             // LastActivityTime not set\n860:         },\n861:     }\n862:     \n863:     client := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithObjects(agentRuntime).Build()\n864:     reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n865:     reconciler.Clock = &fakeClock{now: now}\n866:     \n867:     // Execute\n868:     result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n869:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n870:     })\n871:     \n872:     // Assert - should delete based on creation time\n873:     require.NoError(t, err)\n874:     assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n875:     \n876:     // Verify resource deleted\n877:     err = client.Get(context.Background(), types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n878:     require.Error(t, err)\n879:     assert.True(t, errors.IsNotFound(err))\n880: }\n881: \n882: func TestCheckIdleTimeout_NoTimeout(t *testing.T) {\n883:     now := time.Now()\n884:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n885:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n886:             // IdleTimeoutSeconds not set\n887:         },\n888:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n889:             LastActivityTime: &metav1.Time{Time: now.Add(-1 * time.Hour)},\n890:         },\n891:     }\n892:     \n893:     result, err := CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime, now)\n894:     require.NoError(t, err)\n895:     assert.False(t, result.ShouldDelete)\n896:     assert.Equal(t, \"no idle timeout configured\", result.Reason)\n897: }\n898: \n899: func TestCheckIdleTimeout_NotExpired(t *testing.T) {\n900:     now := time.Now()\n901:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n902:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n903:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](1800), // 30 minutes\n904:         },\n905:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n906:             LastActivityTime: &metav1.Time{Time: now.Add(-10 * time.Minute)},\n907:         },\n908:     }\n909:     \n910:     result, err := CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime, now)\n911:     require.NoError(t, err)\n912:     assert.False(t, result.ShouldDelete)\n913:     assert.InDelta(t, 20*time.Minute, result.RemainingTime, float64(time.Second))\n914: }\n915: \n916: func TestCheckIdleTimeout_Expired(t *testing.T) {\n917:     now := time.Now()\n918:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n919:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n920:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](600), // 10 minutes\n921:         },\n922:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n923:             LastActivityTime: &metav1.Time{Time: now.Add(-15 * time.Minute)},\n924:         },\n925:     }\n926:     \n927:     result, err := CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime, now)\n928:     require.NoError(t, err)\n929:     assert.True(t, result.ShouldDelete)\n930:     assert.Equal(t, \"idle timeout exceeded\", result.Reason)\n931:     assert.InDelta(t, 15*time.Minute, result.IdleDuration, float64(time.Second))\n932: }\n933: \n934: // fakeClock implements Clock for testing\n935: type fakeClock struct {\n936:     now time.Time\n937: }\n938: \n939: func (c *fakeClock) Now() time.Time {\n940:     return c.now\n941: }\n942: ```\n943: \n944: #### config_test.go\n945: \n946: ```go\n947: func TestLoadConfig_Defaults(t *testing.T) {\n948:     cfg, err := LoadConfig()\n949:     require.NoError(t, err)\n950:     \n951:     assert.True(t, cfg.LeaderElection)\n952:     assert.Equal(t, 10*time.Minute, cfg.SyncPeriod)\n953:     assert.Equal(t, 1, cfg.WorkerCount)\n954:     assert.Equal(t, 15*time.Minute, cfg.IdleTimeout.DefaultTimeout)\n955: }\n956: \n957: func TestLoadConfig_FromEnv(t *testing.T) {\n958:     t.Setenv(\"AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT\", \"30m\")\n959:     t.Setenv(\"AGENTD_WORKER_COUNT\", \"5\")\n960:     t.Setenv(\"AGENTD_LEADER_ELECTION\", \"false\")\n961:     \n962:     cfg, err := LoadConfig()\n963:     require.NoError(t, err)\n964:     \n965:     assert.Equal(t, 30*time.Minute, cfg.IdleTimeout.DefaultTimeout)\n966:     assert.Equal(t, 5, cfg.WorkerCount)\n967:     assert.False(t, cfg.LeaderElection)\n968: }\n969: \n970: func TestIdleTimeoutConfig_Validate(t *testing.T) {\n971:     // Valid config\n972:     validConfig := IdleTimeoutConfig{\n973:         DefaultTimeout: 15 * time.Minute,\n974:         MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n975:         MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n976:     }\n977:     require.NoError(t, validConfig.Validate())\n978:     \n979:     // Invalid: default < min\n980:     invalidConfig1 := IdleTimeoutConfig{\n981:         DefaultTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n982:         MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n983:         MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n984:     }\n985:     require.Error(t, invalidConfig1.Validate())\n986:     \n987:     // Invalid: default > max\n988:     invalidConfig2 := IdleTimeoutConfig{\n989:         DefaultTimeout: 48 * time.Hour,\n990:         MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n991:         MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n992:     }\n993:     require.Error(t, invalidConfig2.Validate())\n994: }\n995: ```\n996: \n997: ### Integration Tests\n998: \n999: ```go\n1000: func TestIntegration_Controller(t *testing.T) {\n1001:     if testing.Short() {\n1002:         t.Skip(\"Skipping integration test\")\n1003:     }\n1004:     \n1005:     // Setup test environment\n1006:     cfg := &rest.Config{Host: os.Getenv(\"KUBECONFIG\")}\n1007:     scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n1008:     require.NoError(t, runtimev1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme))\n1009:     \n1010:     // Create manager\n1011:     mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(cfg, ctrl.Options{\n1012:         Scheme: scheme,\n1013:     })\n1014:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1015:     \n1016:     // Setup reconciler\n1017:     reconciler := NewReconciler(mgr.GetClient(), mgr.GetScheme())\n1018:     require.NoError(t, reconciler.SetupWithManager(mgr))\n1019:     \n1020:     // Create test AgentRuntime\n1021:     ctx := context.Background()\n1022:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n1023:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n1024:             Name:      \"test-idle-cleanup\",\n1025:             Namespace: \"default\",\n1026:         },\n1027:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n1028:             Image:              \"test:latest\",\n1029:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](60), // 1 minute\n1030:         },\n1031:     }\n1032:     \n1033:     err = mgr.GetClient().Create(ctx, agentRuntime)\n1034:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1035:     \n1036:     // Update status with old last activity time\n1037:     agentRuntime.Status.LastActivityTime = &metav1.Time{\n1038:         Time: time.Now().Add(-2 * time.Minute), // 2 minutes ago\n1039:     }\n1040:     err = mgr.GetClient().Status().Update(ctx, agentRuntime)\n1041:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1042:     \n1043:     // Trigger reconciliation\n1044:     _, err = reconciler.Reconcile(ctx, reconcile.Request{\n1045:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test-idle-cleanup\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n1046:     })\n1047:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1048:     \n1049:     // Verify deletion\n1050:     err = mgr.GetClient().Get(ctx, types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test-idle-cleanup\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n1051:     require.Error(t, err)\n1052:     assert.True(t, errors.IsNotFound(err))\n1053: }\n1054: ```\n1055: \n1056: ### Test Execution\n1057: \n1058: ```bash\n1059: # Run all controller tests\n1060: make test PKG=./pkg/agentd/...\n1061: \n1062: # Run with race detector\n1063: go test -race ./pkg/agentd/...\n1064: \n1065: # Run specific test categories\n1066: go test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -run \"TestReconciler\"\n1067: go test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -run \"TestCheckIdleTimeout\"\n1068: go test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -run \"TestLoadConfig\"\n1069: \n1070: # With coverage\n1071: go test ./pkg/agentd/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\n1072: go tool cover -html=coverage.out\n1073: \n1074: # Integration tests (requires k8s cluster)\n1075: go test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -tags=integration\n1076: ```\n1077: \n1078: ---\n1079: \n1080: ## Security Considerations\n1081: \n1082: ### Resource Deletion\n1083: \n1084: - Deletion uses foreground propagation for graceful cleanup\n1085: - Only deletes resources in the same namespace the controller has access to\n1086: - RBAC rules must be carefully configured to allow only delete on AgentRuntime\n1087: - Audit logging should be enabled for deletion events\n1088: \n1089: ### RBAC Requirements\n1090: \n1091: ```yaml\n1092: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n1093: kind: ClusterRole\n1094: metadata:\n1095:   name: agentd-idle-cleanup\n1096: rules:\n1097: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n1098:   resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n1099:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]\n1100: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n1101:   resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]\n1102:   verbs: [\"get\"]\n1103: ```\n1104: \n1105: ### Time Safety\n1106: \n1107: - Clock skew between controller and API server is handled via configurable tolerance\n1108: - Time comparisons use monotonic clocks where available\n1109: - Leap seconds are handled gracefully\n1110: \n1111: ### Logging Safety\n1112: \n1113: - Resource names and namespaces are logged at appropriate levels\n1114: - No sensitive data (tokens, credentials) is logged\n1115: - Log levels: DEBUG (V(2)) for timing details, INFO for deletions, WARN for errors\n1116: \n1117: ---\n1118: \n1119: ## Performance Considerations\n1120: \n1121: ### Scalability\n1122: \n1123: | Metric | Target | Notes |\n1124: |--------|--------|-------|\n1125: | Reconcile latency | < 100ms | P99 for single resource |\n1126: | Concurrent reconciles | 10+ | Configurable via worker count |\n1127: | Memory per resource | < 1KB | Minimal resource footprint |\n1128: | API calls per reconcile | 1-2 | Get + optional Delete |\n1129: \n1130: ### Optimization Strategies\n1131: \n1132: - Single API call per reconcile (Get only, Delete only when needed)\n1133: - Precise requeue timing based on remaining idle time\n1134: - No polling - event-driven reconciliation\n1135: - Minimal memory allocation in hot path\n1136: - Shared informer cache for reduced API server load\n1137: \n1138: ### Resource Usage\n1139: \n1140: - **Memory**: Scales with number of AgentRuntimes being watched\n1141: - **CPU**: Low baseline, spikes during bulk reconciliations\n1142: - **Network**: Minimal - only API calls for Get and Delete\n1143: - **Storage**: None (no persistent storage)\n1144: \n1145: ---\n1146: \n1147: ## Integration Points\n1148: \n1149: ### With AgentRuntime API\n1150: \n1151: ```go\n1152: // Watches AgentRuntime resources via controller-runtime\n1153: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n1154:     return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n1155:         For(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}).\n1156:         WithEventFilter(predicate.GenerationChangedPredicate{}).\n1157:         Complete(r)\n1158: }\n1159: ```\n1160: \n1161: ### With client-go\n1162: \n1163: ```go\n1164: // Uses generated client for typed operations\n1165: import runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n1166: \n1167: // Get AgentRuntime using controller-runtime client (wrapper around client-go)\n1168: err := r.client.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, agentRuntime)\n1169: ```\n1170: \n1171: ### With Workload Manager\n1172: \n1173: The controller reads `LastActivityTime` which is updated by the workload manager:\n1174: \n1175: ```go\n1176: // LastActivityTime is set by workload manager when processing requests\n1177: lastActivity := agentRuntime.Status.LastActivityTime\n1178: ```\n1179: \n1180: ### With Metrics Server\n1181: \n1182: ```go\n1183: // Metrics are exposed for Prometheus scraping\n1184: metrics.Registry.MustRegister(reconciler.Metrics.ReconcileTotal)\n1185: metrics.Registry.MustRegister(reconciler.Metrics.CleanupTotal)\n1186: ```\n1187: \n1188: ---\n1189: \n1190: ## Dependencies\n1191: \n1192: ```go\n1193: import (\n1194:     \"context\"\n1195:     \"errors\"\n1196:     \"fmt\"\n1197:     \"os\"\n1198:     \"time\"\n1199:     \n1200:     \"github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus\"\n1201:     corev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n1202:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n1203:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n1204:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n1205:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/types\"\n1206:     \"k8s.io/utils/ptr\"\n1207:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n1208:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/log\"\n1209:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/manager\"\n1210:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/reconcile\"\n1211:     \n1212:     runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n1213: )\n1214: ```\n1215: \n1216: | Package | Purpose | Version |\n1217: |---------|---------|---------|\n1218: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Controller framework | v0.19.x |\n1219: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | Metrics | v1.20.x |\n1220: | `k8s.io/api` | Kubernetes API types | v0.31.x |\n1221: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Kubernetes utilities | v0.31.x |\n1222: | `k8s.io/utils` | Kubernetes helpers | v0.0.x |\n1223: \n1224: ---\n1225: \n1226: ## References\n1227: \n1228: - [AgentRuntime Types](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go) — AgentRuntime CRD types\n1229: - [client-go Spec](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/.sdd_prompt.md) — client-go library specification\n1230: - [Idle Cleanup (Sandbox)](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli-benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/design.md) — Related sandbox idle cleanup design\n1231: - [controller-runtime](https://pkg.go.dev/sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime) — Controller runtime documentation\n1232: - [Kubernetes Controllers](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/architecture/controller/) — Kubernetes controller patterns\n1233: \n1234: ---\n1235: \n1236: *AR-018 — Module: pkg/agentd — Language: Go — Size: S*\n\n(End of file - total 1236 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-018 Design: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-018  \n**Module:** `pkg/agentd`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S (Small)\n\nThe Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller is a Kubernetes controller that automatically deletes AgentRuntime resources that have exceeded their configured idle timeout. It monitors the `LastActivityTime` field in AgentRuntime status and compares it against the `IdleTimeoutSeconds` specified in the spec to determine when a resource should be cleaned up.\n\nThis implementation integrates with:\n- **AgentRuntime API (pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1)**: Watches AgentRuntime resources\n- **client-go library**: Uses generated Kubernetes clientset for API interactions\n- **controller-runtime**: Manages the controller lifecycle and reconciliation loop\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775897101779,"end":1775897101798}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897101818,"sessionID":"ses_284491adcffeLHpQLAseZVZ6d5","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb73cd4001mZjGz0ZTE17xkc","messageID":"msg_d7bb7260f001EEonoUn4YYImRr","sessionID":"ses_284491adcffeLHpQLAseZVZ6d5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cli-toolkit/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cli-toolkit/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Design\n2: \n3: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`.\n4: \n5: ## Package layout (every module path and role)\n6: \n7: | Path | Role |\n8: |------|------|\n9: | `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n10: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n11: | `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n12: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, all commands, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n13: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n14: | `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n15: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` |\n16: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` |\n17: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` |\n18: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` |\n19: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` |\n20: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |\n21: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` |\n22: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` |\n23: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` |\n24: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` |\n25: | `agentcube/operations/__init__.py` | Placeholder module docstring (no symbols) |\n26: | `examples/hello-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n27: | `examples/math-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n28: \n29: **Setuptools packages** (from `pyproject.toml` `[tool.setuptools]`):  \n30: `agentcube`, `agentcube.cli`, `agentcube.runtime`, `agentcube.operations`, `agentcube.services`  \n31: *(Note: `agentcube.models` is not listed in `[tool.setuptools] packages` but is imported; packaging may rely on setuptools discovery for subpackages — reconstruct imports from source as above.)*\n32: \n33: ## Console script entry point\n34: \n35: ```toml\n36: [project.scripts]\n37: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n38: ```\n39: \n40: Typer app object: `app = typer.Typer(name=\"agentcube\", help=\"...\", no_args_is_help=True, rich_markup_mode=\"rich\", add_completion=False)`.\n41: \n42: ## Typer — root callback\n43: \n44: ```python\n45: def main(\n46:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n47:         None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\",\n48:         callback=version_callback, is_eager=True,\n49:     ),\n50:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n51: ) -> None:\n52:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n53: ```\n54: \n55: ## Typer — `pack`\n56: \n57: ```python\n58: def pack(\n59:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n60:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n61:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n62:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n63:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n64:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n65:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n66:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n67:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n68: ) -> None:\n69: ```\n70: \n71: ## Typer — `build`\n72: \n73: ```python\n74: def build(\n75:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n76:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n77:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n78:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n79:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n80: ) -> None:\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ## Typer — `publish`\n84: \n85: ```python\n86: def publish(\n87:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n88:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n89:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n90:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n91:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n92:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n93:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n94:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n95:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n96:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n97:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n98:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n99:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n100: ) -> None:\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ## Typer — `invoke`\n104: \n105: ```python\n106: def invoke(\n107:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n108:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n109:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n110:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n111:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n112: ) -> None:\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ## Typer — `status`\n116: \n117: ```python\n118: def status(\n119:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n120:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n121:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n122: ) -> None:\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ## Helper functions (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n126: \n127: ```python\n128: def version_callback(value: bool) -> None: ...\n129: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None: ...  # prints, typer.Exit(1)\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ## Runtime classes\n133: \n134: ### `PackRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n135: \n136: ```python\n137: class PackRuntime:\n138:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n139:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n140:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n141:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n142:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n143:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n144:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n145:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n146:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n147:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n148:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n149:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n150:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n151:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n152:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None: ...\n153:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path: ...\n154:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str: ...\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ### `BuildRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n158: \n159: ```python\n160: class BuildRuntime:\n161:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n162:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n163:     def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n164:     def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n165:     def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n166:     def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n167:     def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None: ...\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### `PublishRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`)\n171: \n172: ```python\n173: class PublishRuntime:\n174:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n175:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n176:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n177:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n178:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n179:     def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n180:     def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n181:     def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n182: ```\n183: \n184: ### `InvokeRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n185: \n186: ```python\n187: class InvokeRuntime:\n188:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n189:     def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any: ...\n190:     def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[Any, str, str]: ...\n191:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], endpoint: str, workspace_path: Path) -> Any: ...\n192:     async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n193: ```\n194: \n195: **Implementation note:** `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` only assigns `response` inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`; if the condition is false, `return response` may raise `UnboundLocalError` (as of extracted source).\n196: \n197: ### `StatusRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n198: \n199: ```python\n200: class StatusRuntime:\n201:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n202:     def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n203:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n204:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n205: ```\n206: \n207: ## `DockerService` (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n208: \n209: ```python\n210: class DockerService:\n211:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n212:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n213:     def build_image(\n214:         self,\n215:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n216:         context_path: Path,\n217:         image_name: str,\n218:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n219:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n220:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n221:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n222:     def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n223:     def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str: ...\n224:     def push_image(\n225:         self,\n226:         image_name: str,\n227:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n228:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n229:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n230:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n231:     def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None: ...\n232:     def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None: ...\n233:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n234: ```\n235: \n236: ## `MetadataService` (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n237: \n238: ```python\n239: class MetadataService:\n240:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n241:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n242:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n243:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n244:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool: ...\n245:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n246:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n247: ```\n248: \n249: ## `KubernetesProvider` (`agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`)\n250: \n251: ```python\n252: class KubernetesProvider:\n253:     def __init__(\n254:         self,\n255:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n256:         verbose: bool = False,\n257:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n258:     ) -> None: ...\n259:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n260:     def deploy_agent(\n261:         self,\n262:         agent_name: str,\n263:         image_url: str,\n264:         port: int,\n265:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n266:         replicas: int = 1,\n267:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n268:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n269:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n270:     def _create_deployment(\n271:         self,\n272:         name: str,\n273:         image_url: str,\n274:         port: int,\n275:         entrypoint: Optional[str],\n276:         replicas: int,\n277:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n278:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n279:     def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n280:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n281:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n282:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n283:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n284: ```\n285: \n286: ## `AgentCubeProvider` (`agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`)\n287: \n288: ```python\n289: class AgentCubeProvider:\n290:     def __init__(\n291:         self,\n292:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n293:         verbose: bool = False,\n294:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n295:     ) -> None: ...\n296:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n297:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n298:         self,\n299:         agent_name: str,\n300:         image_url: str,\n301:         port: int,\n302:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n303:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n304:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n305:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n306:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n307:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n308:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n309:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n310:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n311: ```\n312: \n313: CR API: `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`.\n314: \n315: ## `AgentMetadata` (Pydantic `BaseModel`)\n316: \n317: | Field | Type | Default | `Field(..., description=...)` |\n318: |-------|------|---------|--------------------------------|\n319: | `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n320: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n321: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n322: | `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n323: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n324: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n325: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n326: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string for publishing |\n327: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image information |\n328: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication configuration |\n329: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n330: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for image publishing |\n331: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n332: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n333: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n334: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Workload Manager |\n335: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Router |\n336: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path for the readiness probe |\n337: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port for the readiness probe |\n338: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n339: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The session ID for the agent |\n340: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment information |\n341: \n342: Validators: `validate_language` → `['python','java']` lowercase; `validate_build_mode` → `['local','cloud']` lowercase; `validate_port` → `1..65535`.\n343: \n344: ## `MetadataOptions` (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n345: \n346: Dataclass fields (all `Optional` unless noted):\n347: \n348: | Field | Type | Default |\n349: |-------|------|---------|\n350: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n351: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n352: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n353: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n354: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n355: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n356: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n357: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n358: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n359: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n360: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n361: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n362: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n363: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n364: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n365: \n366: ```python\n367: @classmethod\n368: def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\": ...\n369: ```\n370: \n371: ## Dependencies (`cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`)\n372: \n373: **`[project]` dependencies:**\n374: \n375: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0`\n376: - `pydantic>=2.0.0`\n377: - `pyyaml>=6.0`\n378: - `httpx>=0.24.0`\n379: - `docker>=6.0.0`\n380: - `rich>=13.0.0`\n381: - `packaging>=23.0`\n382: - `importlib-resources>=6.0.0`\n383: - `semver>=3.0.0`\n384: \n385: **Optional `[project.optional-dependencies]`:**\n386: \n387: - `k8s`: `kubernetes>=28.0.0`\n388: - `dev`: `pytest>=7.4.0`, `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0`, `pytest-cov>=4.1.0`, `ruff>=0.1.0`, `mypy>=1.5.0`, `pre-commit>=3.3.0`, `kubernetes>=28.0.0`\n389: - `test`: `pytest>=7.4.0`, `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0`, `pytest-cov>=4.1.0`, `pytest-mock>=3.11.0`, `httpx-mock>=0.10.0`\n390: \n391: **Python:** `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`.\n392: \n393: ## Top-level exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n394: \n395: - `__version__ = \"0.1.0\"`\n396: - `__author__ = \"AgentCube Community\"`\n397: - `__email__ = \"agentcube@volcano.sh\"`\n398: - Imports: `app`, `PackRuntime`, `BuildRuntime`, `PublishRuntime`, `InvokeRuntime`\n399: - `__all__` = `[\"app\", \"PackRuntime\", \"BuildRuntime\", \"PublishRuntime\", \"InvokeRuntime\"]`  \n400:   (`StatusRuntime` is not exported here.)\n\n(End of file - total 400 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Design\n\nSource root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`.\n\n## Package layout (every module path and role)\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n| `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, all commands, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cli-toolkit/design.md","time":{"start":1775897101775,"end":1775897101813}}}}
