{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897117193,"sessionID":"ses_284491adcffeLHpQLAseZVZ6d5","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb778550013USMPaK0tt0qt4","messageID":"msg_d7bb7462f001yKCYtQYwmSWreA","sessionID":"ses_284491adcffeLHpQLAseZVZ6d5","type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"toolu_functions.glob:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"path":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli","pattern":"**/*"},"output":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md","metadata":{"count":1,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli","time":{"start":1775897117173,"end":1775897117191}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897117202,"sessionID":"ses_284491adcffeLHpQLAseZVZ6d5","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb77d16001nCHXXHvhgnSfPd","messageID":"msg_d7bb7462f001yKCYtQYwmSWreA","sessionID":"ses_284491adcffeLHpQLAseZVZ6d5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019 Design: CLI Binary Entry Points\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-019  \n6: **Module:** `cmd`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M (Medium)\n9: \n10: This module provides the CLI binary entry points for the 4 core AgentCube components. Each binary provides a standalone executable that initializes its respective service with proper configuration, dependency wiring, and graceful shutdown handling.\n11: \n12: ### Components\n13: \n14: | Binary | Purpose | Package Dependency |\n15: |--------|---------|-------------------|\n16: | `agentd` | Idle cleanup controller for AgentRuntime resources | `pkg/agentd` |\n17: | `router` | HTTP session routing proxy with JWT authentication | `pkg/router` |\n18: | `workload-manager` | Sandbox orchestration controller with CRD management | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n19: | `picod` | Sandbox daemon for code execution inside sandbox pods | `pkg/picod` |\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Architecture\n24: \n25: ### High-Level Design\n26: \n27: ```\n28: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n29: │                        AgentCube Platform                                    │\n30: │                                                                              │\n31: │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐     │\n32: │  │   agentd     │  │    router    │  │workload-mgr  │  │    picod     │     │\n33: │  │  ┌────────┐  │  │  ┌────────┐  │  │  ┌────────┐  │  │  ┌────────┐  │     │\n34: │  │  │Reconciler│  │  │  │  Gin   │  │  │  │Controller│  │  │  │  HTTP  │  │     │\n35: │  │  │(controller│  │  │  │Server  │  │  │  │ + API    │  │  │  │ Server │  │     │\n36: │  │  │-runtime) │  │  │  │        │  │  │  │ Server   │  │  │  │        │  │     │\n37: │  │  └────┬───┘  │  │  └───┬────┘  │  │  └────┬───┘  │  │  └───┬────┘  │     │\n38: │  │       │      │  │      │       │  │       │      │  │      │       │     │\n39: │  │  K8s API    │  │  Redis/Valkey│  │  K8s API      │  │  Workspace    │     │\n40: │  │       │      │  │      │       │  │       │      │  │      │       │     │\n41: │  └───────┼──────┘  └──────┼───────┘  └───────┼──────┘  └──────┼───────┘     │\n42: │          │                │                  │                │             │\n43: │          └────────────────┴──────────────────┴────────────────┘             │\n44: │                                 │                                           │\n45: │                      Kubernetes Cluster + Redis/Valkey                     │\n46: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### Component Interactions\n50: \n51: ```\n52: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n53: │                        Binary Startup & Integration                          │\n54: │                                                                              │\n55: │  ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐         │\n56: │  │   agentd/main   │    │  router/main    │    │ workload-mgr/main│         │\n57: │  │       │         │    │       │         │    │       │          │         │\n58: │  │       ▼         │    │       ▼         │    │       ▼          │         │\n59: │  │  ┌─────────┐    │    │  ┌─────────┐    │    │  ┌─────────┐     │         │\n60: │  │  │ flag    │    │    │  │ flag    │    │    │  │ flag    │     │         │\n61: │  │  │ parse   │    │    │  │ parse   │    │    │  │ parse   │     │         │\n62: │  │  └────┬────┘    │    │  └────┬────┘    │    │  └────┬────┘     │         │\n63: │  │       ▼         │    │       ▼         │    │       ▼          │         │\n64: │  │  ┌─────────┐    │    │  ┌─────────┐    │    │  ┌─────────┐     │         │\n65: │  │  │ K8s cfg │    │    │  │ Redis   │    │    │  │ K8s cfg │     │         │\n66: │  │  │ client  │    │    │  │ client  │    │    │  │ client  │     │         │\n67: │  │  └────┬────┘    │    │  └────┬────┘    │    │  └────┬────┘     │         │\n68: │  │       ▼         │    │       ▼         │    │       ▼          │         │\n69: │  │  ┌─────────┐    │    │  ┌─────────┐    │    │  ┌─────────┐     │         │\n70: │  │  │Manager  │    │    │  │ Gin     │    │    │  │Manager  │     │         │\n71: │  │  │(ctrl-runtime)│  │    │  │ Server  │    │    │  │(ctrl-runtime)│ │         │\n72: │  │  └────┬────┘    │    │  └────┬────┘    │    │  └────┬────┘     │         │\n73: │  │       ▼         │    │       ▼         │    │       ▼          │         │\n74: │  │  ┌─────────┐    │    │  ┌─────────┐    │    │  ┌─────────┐     │         │\n75: │  │  │Reconciler│   │    │  │Router   │    │    │  │Controller│    │         │\n76: │  │  │(agentd) │    │    │  │Handlers │    │    │  │(workload)│    │         │\n77: │  │  └────┬────┘    │    │  └────┬────┘    │    │  └────┬────┘     │         │\n78: │  │       │         │    │       │         │    │       │          │         │\n79: │  │  client-go      │    │  store pkg      │    │  client-go       │         │\n80: │  │       │         │    │       │         │    │       │          │         │\n81: │  └───────┼─────────┘    └───────┼─────────┘    └───────┼──────────┘         │\n82: │          │                      │                      │                     │\n83: │          └──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┘                     │\n84: │                                 │                                             │\n85: │                          ┌─────────────┐                                      │\n86: │                          │  K8s API    │                                      │\n87: │                          │  Server     │                                      │\n88: │                          └─────────────┘                                      │\n89: │                                                                              │\n90: │  ┌─────────────────┐                                                         │\n91: │  │   picod/main    │                                                         │\n92: │  │       │         │                                                         │\n93: │  │       ▼         │                                                         │\n94: │  │  ┌─────────┐    │                                                         │\n95: │  │  │ flag    │    │                                                         │\n96: │  │  │ parse   │    │                                                         │\n97: │  │  └────┬────┘    │                                                         │\n98: │  │       ▼         │                                                         │\n99: │  │  ┌─────────┐    │                                                         │\n100: │  │  │workspace│    │                                                         │\n101: │  │  │ init    │    │                                                         │\n102: │  │  └────┬────┘    │                                                         │\n103: │  │       ▼         │                                                         │\n104: │  │  ┌─────────┐    │                                                         │\n105: │  │  │ HTTP    │    │                                                         │\n106: │  │  │ Server  │    │                                                         │\n107: │  │  └────┬────┘    │                                                         │\n108: │  │       │         │                                                         │\n109: │  │  pkg/picod      │                                                         │\n110: │  └───────┼─────────┘                                                         │\n111: │          │                                                                   │\n112: │          ▼                                                                   │\n113: │    Sandbox Pod (isolated)                                                    │\n114: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ## Directory Structure\n120: \n121: ```\n122: cmd/\n123: ├── design.md                   # This file\n124: ├── agentd/\n125: │   └── main.go                 # Idle cleanup controller entry point (~80 lines)\n126: ├── router/\n127: │   └── main.go                 # Session routing proxy entry point (~100 lines)\n128: ├── workload-manager/\n129: │   └── main.go                 # Sandbox orchestration entry point (~120 lines)\n130: └── picod/\n131:     └── main.go                 # Sandbox daemon entry point (~90 lines)\n132: ```\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## Data Structures\n137: \n138: ### Common Flag Types\n139: \n140: ```go\n141: // GracefulShutdownConfig holds graceful shutdown configuration.\n142: type GracefulShutdownConfig struct {\n143:     // Timeout is the maximum time to wait for graceful shutdown\n144:     Timeout time.Duration\n145:     // Signals lists the OS signals to handle for graceful shutdown\n146:     Signals []os.Signal\n147: }\n148: \n149: // DefaultGracefulShutdownConfig returns the default configuration.\n150: func DefaultGracefulShutdownConfig() GracefulShutdownConfig {\n151:     return GracefulShutdownConfig{\n152:         Timeout: 30 * time.Second,\n153:         Signals: []os.Signal{syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM},\n154:     }\n155: }\n156: ```\n157: \n158: ### agentd Configuration\n159: \n160: ```go\n161: // AgentdConfig holds the agentd binary configuration.\n162: type AgentdConfig struct {\n163:     // Kubeconfig is the path to kubeconfig file (empty = in-cluster)\n164:     Kubeconfig string\n165:     // SyncPeriod is the full sync period for all AgentRuntimes\n166:     SyncPeriod time.Duration\n167:     // GracefulTimeout is the graceful shutdown timeout\n168:     GracefulTimeout time.Duration\n169: }\n170: \n171: // DefaultAgentdConfig returns the default configuration.\n172: func DefaultAgentdConfig() AgentdConfig {\n173:     return AgentdConfig{\n174:         Kubeconfig:      \"\",\n175:         SyncPeriod:      5 * time.Minute,\n176:         GracefulTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n177:     }\n178: }\n179: ```\n180: \n181: ### router Configuration\n182: \n183: ```go\n184: // RouterConfig holds the router binary configuration.\n185: type RouterConfig struct {\n186:     // Port is the HTTP server port\n187:     Port int\n188:     // Debug enables debug logging\n189:     Debug bool\n190:     // RedisAddr is the Redis/Valkey server address\n191:     RedisAddr string\n192:     // WorkloadManagerURL is the workload manager service URL\n193:     WorkloadManagerURL string\n194:     // GracefulTimeout is the graceful shutdown timeout\n195:     GracefulTimeout time.Duration\n196: }\n197: \n198: // DefaultRouterConfig returns the default configuration.\n199: func DefaultRouterConfig() RouterConfig {\n200:     return RouterConfig{\n201:         Port:            8080,\n202:         Debug:           false,\n203:         GracefulTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n204:     }\n205: }\n206: ```\n207: \n208: ### workload-manager Configuration\n209: \n210: ```go\n211: // WorkloadManagerConfig holds the workload-manager binary configuration.\n212: type WorkloadManagerConfig struct {\n213:     // Port is the HTTP API server port\n214:     Port int\n215:     // Kubeconfig is the path to kubeconfig file (empty = in-cluster)\n216:     Kubeconfig string\n217:     // RedisAddr is the Redis/Valkey server address\n218:     RedisAddr string\n219:     // DefaultImage is the default sandbox image\n220:     DefaultImage string\n221:     // Namespace is the default namespace for resources\n222:     Namespace string\n223:     // GracefulTimeout is the graceful shutdown timeout\n224:     GracefulTimeout time.Duration\n225: }\n226: \n227: // DefaultWorkloadManagerConfig returns the default configuration.\n228: func DefaultWorkloadManagerConfig() WorkloadManagerConfig {\n229:     return WorkloadManagerConfig{\n230:         Port:            8080,\n231:         DefaultImage:    \"ubuntu:22.04\",\n232:         Namespace:       \"default\",\n233:         GracefulTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n234:     }\n235: }\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ### picod Configuration\n239: \n240: ```go\n241: // PicodConfig holds the picod binary configuration.\n242: type PicodConfig struct {\n243:     // Port is the HTTP server port\n244:     Port int\n245:     // Workspace is the workspace root directory\n246:     Workspace string\n247:     // ReadHeaderTimeout is the HTTP read header timeout\n248:     ReadHeaderTimeout time.Duration\n249: }\n250: \n251: // DefaultPicodConfig returns the default configuration.\n252: func DefaultPicodConfig() PicodConfig {\n253:     return PicodConfig{\n254:         Port:              8080,\n255:         Workspace:         \".\",\n256:         ReadHeaderTimeout: 10 * time.Second,\n257:     }\n258: }\n259: ```\n260: \n261: ---\n262: \n263: ## API Contracts\n264: \n265: ### Binary Entry Points\n266: \n267: Each binary follows the same basic structure:\n268: \n269: ```go\n270: func main() {\n271:     // 1. Parse flags\n272:     config := parseFlags()\n273:     \n274:     // 2. Validate configuration\n275:     if err := validateConfig(config); err != nil {\n276:         fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: %v\\n\", err)\n277:         os.Exit(1)\n278:     }\n279:     \n280:     // 3. Log startup\n281:     logStartup(binaryName, version, config)\n282:     \n283:     // 4. Initialize dependencies\n284:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n285:     \n286:     // 5. Start service (blocking)\n287:     if err := run(ctx, config); err != nil {\n288:         fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: %v\\n\", err)\n289:         os.Exit(3)\n290:     }\n291: }\n292: ```\n293: \n294: ### Service Startup Interface\n295: \n296: ```go\n297: // Runnable represents a service that can be started and stopped.\n298: type Runnable interface {\n299:     // Start begins the service and blocks until context cancellation or error.\n300:     Start(ctx context.Context) error\n301:     // Stop initiates graceful shutdown with the given timeout.\n302:     Stop(timeout time.Duration) error\n303: }\n304: ```\n305: \n306: ### Flag Parsing Contract\n307: \n308: All binaries use the standard Go `flag` package:\n309: \n310: | Binary | Flag | Type | Default | Required | Description |\n311: |--------|------|------|---------|----------|-------------|\n312: | agentd | `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | No | Path to kubeconfig |\n313: | agentd | `--sync-period` | duration | 5m | No | Full sync period |\n314: | agentd | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | No | Shutdown timeout |\n315: | router | `--port` | int | 8080 | No | HTTP server port |\n316: | router | `--debug` | bool | false | No | Debug logging |\n317: | router | `--redis-addr` | string | \"\" | **Yes** | Redis address |\n318: | router | `--workload-manager` | string | \"\" | **Yes** | Workload manager URL |\n319: | router | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | No | Shutdown timeout |\n320: | workload-manager | `--port` | int | 8080 | No | HTTP API port |\n321: | workload-manager | `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | No | Path to kubeconfig |\n322: | workload-manager | `--redis-addr` | string | \"\" | **Yes** | Redis address |\n323: | workload-manager | `--default-image` | string | ubuntu:22.04 | No | Default image |\n324: | workload-manager | `--namespace` | string | default | No | Default namespace |\n325: | workload-manager | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | No | Shutdown timeout |\n326: | picod | `--port` | int | 8080 | No | HTTP server port |\n327: | picod | `--workspace` | string | . | No | Workspace directory |\n328: | picod | `--read-header-timeout` | duration | 10s | No | Read header timeout |\n329: \n330: ### Kubernetes Client Integration\n331: \n332: Binaries that interact with Kubernetes use the client-go library defined in `deployment/client-go.md`:\n333: \n334: ```go\n335: // createK8sClient creates a Kubernetes client from configuration.\n336: func createK8sClient(kubeconfig string) (*kubernetes.Clientset, error) {\n337:     // Build config from kubeconfig or in-cluster\n338:     config, err := clientcmd.NewNonInteractiveDeferredLoadingClientConfig(\n339:         &clientcmd.ClientConfigLoadingRules{ExplicitPath: kubeconfig},\n340:         &clientcmd.ConfigOverrides{},\n341:     ).ClientConfig()\n342:     if err != nil {\n343:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to load kubeconfig: %w\", err)\n344:     }\n345:     \n346:     // Create clientset\n347:     clientset, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n348:     if err != nil {\n349:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create clientset: %w\", err)\n350:     }\n351:     \n352:     return clientset, nil\n353: }\n354: ```\n355: \n356: ### controller-runtime Integration\n357: \n358: ```go\n359: // createManager creates a controller-runtime manager.\n360: func createManager(kubeconfig string, syncPeriod time.Duration) (ctrl.Manager, error) {\n361:     config, err := ctrl.GetConfig()\n362:     if err != nil {\n363:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get config: %w\", err)\n364:     }\n365:     \n366:     mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(config, ctrl.Options{\n367:         Scheme:     scheme,\n368:         SyncPeriod: &syncPeriod,\n369:     })\n370:     if err != nil {\n371:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create manager: %w\", err)\n372:     }\n373:     \n374:     return mgr, nil\n375: }\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ---\n379: \n380: ## Error Handling\n381: \n382: ### Error Types\n383: \n384: | Error | Code | Description | Binary |\n385: |-------|------|-------------|--------|\n386: | `FlagError` | 1 | Missing or invalid CLI flags | All |\n387: | `ConfigError` | 1 | Configuration loading failure | agentd, workload-manager |\n388: | `ConnectionError` | 2 | Redis/Valkey connection failure | router, workload-manager |\n389: | `SchemeError` | 2 | CRD scheme registration failure | agentd, workload-manager |\n390: | `ServerError` | 3 | HTTP server startup failure | router, workload-manager, picod |\n391: | `WorkspaceError` | 2 | Workspace initialization failure | picod |\n392: \n393: ### Exit Codes\n394: \n395: | Exit Code | Meaning |\n396: |-----------|---------|\n397: | 0 | Clean shutdown |\n398: | 1 | Configuration error |\n399: | 2 | Dependency initialization error |\n400: | 3 | Server startup error |\n401: | 130 | Interrupted (SIGINT) |\n402: | 143 | Terminated (SIGTERM) |\n403: \n404: ### Error Propagation\n405: \n406: ```go\n407: // FatalError represents an error that should cause immediate exit.\n408: type FatalError struct {\n409:     Code    int\n410:     Message string\n411:     Cause   error\n412: }\n413: \n414: func (e *FatalError) Error() string {\n415:     if e.Cause != nil {\n416:         return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %v\", e.Message, e.Cause)\n417:     }\n418:     return e.Message\n419: }\n420: \n421: // Wrap wraps an error with a fatal error code.\n422: func Wrap(code int, message string, err error) *FatalError {\n423:     return &FatalError{Code: code, Message: message, Cause: err}\n424: }\n425: ```\n426: \n427: ---\n428: \n429: ## Testing Strategy\n430: \n431: ### Unit Testing\n432: \n433: ```go\n434: // Test flag parsing\n435: func TestParseFlags(t *testing.T) {\n436:     tests := []struct {\n437:         name     string\n438:         args     []string\n439:         expected Config\n440:         wantErr  bool\n441:     }{\n442:         {\n443:             name: \"default values\",\n444:             args: []string{\"cmd\"},\n445:             expected: Config{\n446:                 Port: 8080,\n447:                 // ...\n448:             },\n449:         },\n450:         // ...\n451:     }\n452:     // ...\n453: }\n454: ```\n455: \n456: ### Integration Testing\n457: \n458: | Test | Command | Expected |\n459: |------|---------|----------|\n460: | Build | `go build ./cmd/agentd/...` | Binary compiles |\n461: | Help | `./bin/agentd --help` | Usage printed, exit 0 |\n462: | Missing flags | `./bin/router` | Error printed, exit 1 |\n463: | Graceful shutdown | `timeout 2 ./bin/picod` | Exit 0 |\n464: \n465: ### Build Verification\n466: \n467: ```bash\n468: # Build all binaries\n469: go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n470: go build -o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/router\n471: go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n472: go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n473: \n474: # Verify binaries exist\n475: ls -la bin/\n476: ```\n477: \n478: ---\n479: \n480: ## Dependencies\n481: \n482: ### External Dependencies\n483: \n484: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n485: |---------|---------|---------|\n486: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.19.0 | Kubernetes controller framework |\n487: | `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes client library |\n488: | `k8s.io/api` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes API types |\n489: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes API machinery |\n490: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | latest | HTTP framework for router |\n491: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.7.3 | Redis client |\n492: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | v1.0.56 | Valkey client |\n493: \n494: ### Internal Dependencies\n495: \n496: | Package | Purpose |\n497: |---------|---------|\n498: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd` | Idle cleanup reconciler |\n499: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router` | Session routing handlers |\n500: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` | Sandbox orchestration |\n501: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` | Sandbox daemon |\n502: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | CRD types |\n503: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Redis/Valkey store |\n504: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated Kubernetes client |\n505: \n506: ---\n507: \n508: ## Integration with client-go\n509: \n510: The binaries that interact with Kubernetes use the generated client-go library from `deployment/client-go.md`:\n511: \n512: ### Clientset Usage\n513: \n514: ```go\n515: import (\n516:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n517:     runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n518: )\n519: \n520: // Create clientset\n521: config, _ := ctrl.GetConfig()\n522: clientset, _ := versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n523: \n524: // Access typed clients\n525: agentRuntimes := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace)\n526: codeInterpreters := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace)\n527: ```\n528: \n529: ### Informer Usage\n530: \n531: ```go\n532: import (\n533:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/informers/externalversions\"\n534: )\n535: \n536: // Create informer factory\n537: factory := externalversions.NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, 5*time.Minute)\n538: \n539: // Get informers\n540: agentRuntimeInformer := factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes()\n541: codeInterpreterInformer := factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters()\n542: ```\n543: \n544: ---\n545: \n546: ## Performance Characteristics\n547: \n548: | Binary | Memory (est.) | Startup Time | Notes |\n549: |--------|---------------|--------------|-------|\n550: | agentd | ~50MB | <5s | Reconciler only, no HTTP server |\n551: | router | ~30MB | <3s | Depends on Redis connection |\n552: | workload-manager | ~60MB | <5s | Controller + HTTP server |\n553: | picod | ~20MB | <2s | Lightweight daemon |\n554: \n555: ---\n556: \n557: ## Security Considerations\n558: \n559: ### RBAC Requirements\n560: \n561: #### agentd\n562: | Resource | API Group | Verbs |\n563: |----------|-----------|-------|\n564: | `agentruntimes` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `delete` |\n565: | `agentruntimes/status` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `update`, `patch` |\n566: \n567: #### router\n568: | Resource | API Group | Verbs |\n569: |----------|-----------|-------|\n570: | `secrets` | \"\" | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n571: \n572: #### workload-manager\n573: | Resource | API Group | Verbs |\n574: |----------|-----------|-------|\n575: | `agentruntimes` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n576: | `codeinterpreters` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n577: | `codeinterpreters/status` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `get`, `update`, `patch` |\n578: | `pods` | \"\" | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n579: | `secrets` | \"\" | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n580: \n581: #### picod\n582: - Runs inside sandbox pod with container-local permissions\n583: - Workspace directory isolation\n584: - No Kubernetes API access required\n585: \n586: ### Sensitive Data Handling\n587: - Redis passwords via environment variables (not flags)\n588: - Kubernetes service account tokens (in-cluster) or kubeconfig files\n589: - No secrets logged at startup\n590: \n591: ---\n592: \n593: ## Build and Deployment\n594: \n595: ### Makefile Targets\n596: \n597: | Target | Description |\n598: |--------|-------------|\n599: | `build-agentd` | Build agentd binary |\n600: | `build-router` | Build router binary |\n601: | `build` | Build workload-manager binary (default) |\n602: | `build-all` | Build all binaries |\n603: | `run` | Run workload-manager locally |\n604: | `run-router` | Run router locally |\n605: | `docker-build` | Build workload-manager Docker image |\n606: | `docker-build-router` | Build router Docker image |\n607: | `docker-build-picod` | Build picod Docker image |\n608: \n609: ### Docker Images\n610: \n611: | Binary | Dockerfile | Image Name |\n612: |--------|------------|------------|\n613: | workload-manager | `docker/Dockerfile` | `workloadmanager:latest` |\n614: | router | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | `agentcube-router:latest` |\n615: | picod | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | `picod:latest` |\n616: \n617: ---\n618: \n619: ## References\n620: \n621: - [client-go Library](../deployment/client-go.md) — Generated Kubernetes client\n622: - [Deployment Design](../deployment/design.md) — Helm charts and Dockerfiles\n623: - [project.md](../project.md) — Project context and architecture\n624: - [pkg/agentd](../pkg/agentd/) — Idle cleanup controller package\n625: - [pkg/router](../pkg/router/) — Session routing package\n626: - [pkg/workloadmanager](../pkg/workloadmanager/) — Sandbox orchestration package\n627: - [pkg/picod](../pkg/picod/) — Sandbox daemon package\n\n(End of file - total 627 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019 Design: CLI Binary Entry Points\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-019  \n**Module:** `cmd`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M (Medium)\n\nThis module provides the CLI binary entry points for the 4 core AgentCube components. Each binary provides a standalone executable that initializes its respective service with proper configuration, dependency wiring, and graceful shutdown handling.\n\n### Components\n\n| Binary | Purpose | Package Dependency |\n|--------|---------|-------------------|\n| `agentd` | Idle cleanup controller for AgentRuntime resources | `pkg/agentd` |\n| `router` | HTTP session routing proxy with JWT authentication | `pkg/router` |\n| `workload-manager` | Sandbox orchestration controller with CRD management | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| `picod` | Sandbox daemon for code execution inside sandbox pods | `pkg/picod` |\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/design.md","time":{"start":1775897117176,"end":1775897117198}}}}
