{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897150273,"sessionID":"ses_284491adcffeLHpQLAseZVZ6d5","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb7feea001cSob0yRz844uwK","messageID":"msg_d7bb78244001AEFDarm2sGg2qx","sessionID":"ses_284491adcffeLHpQLAseZVZ6d5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024: DockerService Encapsulation — Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document provides technical implementation details for the `DockerService` component in the AgentCube CLI project. The DockerService provides a high-level abstraction over the Docker SDK for building, managing, and publishing container images.\n6: \n7: **AR:** AR-024  \n8: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n9: **Language:** Python  \n10: **Size:** M\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Architecture\n15: \n16: ### Component Diagram\n17: \n18: ```\n19: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n20: │                            CLI Layer                                          │\n21: │  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────┐                         │\n22: │  │   build command     │    │   publish command   │                         │\n23: │  │   (main.py)         │    │   (main.py)         │                         │\n24: │  └──────────┬──────────┘    └──────────┬──────────┘                         │\n25: │             │                          │                                     │\n26: │             ▼                          ▼                                     │\n27: │  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────┐                         │\n28: │  │   BuildRuntime      │    │   PublishRuntime    │                         │\n29: │  │   (build_runtime)   │    │   (publish_runtime) │                         │\n30: │  └──────────┬──────────┘    └──────────┬──────────┘                         │\n31: └─────────────┼──────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────┘\n32:               │                          │\n33:               ▼                          ▼\n34: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n35: │                          Service Layer                                        │\n36: │                    ┌─────────────────────┐                                    │\n37: │                    │    DockerService    │                                    │\n38: │                    │   (docker_service)  │                                    │\n39: │                    └──────────┬──────────┘                                    │\n40: │                               │                                               │\n41: │              ┌────────────────┼────────────────┐                              │\n42: │              ▼                ▼                ▼                              │\n43: │    ┌─────────────────┐ ┌─────────────┐ ┌───────────────┐                      │\n44: │    │  Build Image    │ │ Push Image  │ │  Remove Image │                      │\n45: │    └────────┬────────┘ └──────┬──────┘ └───────┬───────┘                      │\n46: │             │                 │                │                              │\n47: └─────────────┼─────────────────┼────────────────┼──────────────────────────────┘\n48:               │                 │                │\n49:               ▼                 ▼                ▼\n50: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n51: │                         Docker Engine API                                     │\n52: │                    (docker.from_env() SDK)                                   │\n53: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n54: ```\n55: \n56: ### Data Flow\n57: \n58: #### Build Image Flow\n59: ```\n60: 1. BuildRuntime calls DockerService.build_image()\n61: 2. DockerService validates Docker is available\n62: 3. Calls Docker SDK to build image from Dockerfile\n63: 4. Streams build logs (if verbose)\n64: 5. Returns image info (name, id, size, build_time)\n65: ```\n66: \n67: #### Push Image Flow\n68: ```\n69: 1. PublishRuntime calls DockerService.push_image()\n70: 2. If credentials provided, login to registry\n71: 3. Tag image for target registry (if needed)\n72: 4. Push image with streaming logs\n73: 5. Return push confirmation with timestamp\n74: ```\n75: \n76: #### Remove Image Flow\n77: ```\n78: 1. BuildRuntime/PublishRuntime calls DockerService.remove_image()\n79: 2. Attempt to remove image by name\n80: 3. Return True on success, False on failure\n81: 4. Log warning on failure (non-blocking)\n82: ```\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## Module Structure\n87: \n88: ### File Layout\n89: \n90: | Path | Role |\n91: |------|------|\n92: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` class - Docker SDK wrapper |\n93: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package marker |\n94: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Uses DockerService for image building |\n95: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Uses DockerService for image pushing |\n96: \n97: ### Dependencies\n98: \n99: ```\n100: DockerService\n101:     ├── docker (Docker SDK for Python)\n102:     ├── pathlib (Path handling)\n103:     └── typing (Type hints)\n104: \n105: BuildRuntime\n106:     └── DockerService (for local builds)\n107: \n108: PublishRuntime\n109:     └── DockerService (for image preparation and push)\n110: ```\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ## Implementation Details\n115: \n116: ### 1. DockerService (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n117: \n118: #### Class Definition\n119: \n120: ```python\n121: class DockerService:\n122:     \"\"\"Service class for Docker operations.\n123:     \n124:     Provides high-level abstraction over Docker SDK for:\n125:     - Image building from Dockerfiles\n126:     - Image inspection and information retrieval\n127:     - Image pushing to registries\n128:     - Image cleanup/removal\n129:     \"\"\"\n130:     \n131:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n132:         self.verbose = verbose\n133:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n134:         self._client: Optional[docker.DockerClient] = None\n135:     \n136:     @property\n137:     def client(self) -> docker.DockerClient:\n138:         \"\"\"Lazy initialization of Docker client.\"\"\"\n139:         if self._client is None:\n140:             self._client = docker.from_env()\n141:         return self._client\n142: ```\n143: \n144: #### Key Methods\n145: \n146: **`check_docker_available`**\n147: ```python\n148: def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n149:     \"\"\"Check if Docker daemon is accessible.\n150:     \n151:     Returns:\n152:         True if Docker is available, False otherwise.\n153:         \n154:     Raises:\n155:         RuntimeError: If Docker is not available (when used in build context).\n156:     \"\"\"\n157:     try:\n158:         self.client.ping()\n159:         return True\n160:     except docker.errors.DockerException as e:\n161:         self.logger.error(f\"Docker is not available: {e}\")\n162:         return False\n163: ```\n164: \n165: **`build_image`**\n166: ```python\n167: def build_image(\n168:     self,\n169:     dockerfile_path: Path,\n170:     context_path: Path,\n171:     image_name: str,\n172:     tag: str = \"latest\",\n173:     build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n174: ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n175:     \"\"\"Build a Docker image from a Dockerfile.\n176:     \n177:     Args:\n178:         dockerfile_path: Path to the Dockerfile\n179:         context_path: Build context directory\n180:         image_name: Name for the built image\n181:         tag: Image tag (default: \"latest\")\n182:         build_args: Optional build arguments\n183:         \n184:     Returns:\n185:         Dict containing:\n186:         - image_name: Full image name with tag\n187:         - image_id: Docker image ID\n188:         - image_size: Human-readable image size\n189:         - build_time: ISO format timestamp\n190:         \n191:     Raises:\n192:         RuntimeError: If Docker is unavailable or build fails\n193:         docker.errors.BuildError: If image build fails\n194:     \"\"\"\n195:     if not self.check_docker_available():\n196:         raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n197:     \n198:     build_args = build_args or {}\n199:     full_image_name = f\"{image_name}:{tag}\"\n200:     \n201:     self.logger.info(f\"Building image: {full_image_name}\")\n202:     self.logger.debug(f\"Dockerfile: {dockerfile_path}\")\n203:     self.logger.debug(f\"Context: {context_path}\")\n204:     self.logger.debug(f\"Build args: {build_args}\")\n205:     \n206:     start_time = datetime.now()\n207:     \n208:     try:\n209:         # Build the image with streaming logs\n210:         image, build_logs = self.client.images.build(\n211:             path=str(context_path),\n212:             dockerfile=str(dockerfile_path.relative_to(context_path)),\n213:             tag=full_image_name,\n214:             buildargs=build_args,\n215:             rm=True,\n216:             forcerm=True,\n217:         )\n218:         \n219:         # Stream logs if verbose\n220:         if self.verbose:\n221:             for log_line in build_logs:\n222:                 if 'stream' in log_line:\n223:                     self.logger.debug(log_line['stream'].strip())\n224:         \n225:         build_time = (datetime.now() - start_time).total_seconds()\n226:         \n227:         # Get image info\n228:         image_info = self._get_image_info(full_image_name)\n229:         \n230:         self.logger.info(f\"Successfully built {full_image_name} in {build_time:.2f}s\")\n231:         \n232:         return {\n233:             \"image_name\": full_image_name,\n234:             \"image_id\": image.id,\n235:             \"image_size\": image_info.get(\"size\", \"unknown\"),\n236:             \"build_time\": f\"{build_time:.2f}s\",\n237:         }\n238:         \n239:     except docker.errors.BuildError as e:\n240:         self.logger.error(f\"Build failed: {e}\")\n241:         # Log build output for debugging\n242:         if self.verbose and hasattr(e, 'build_log'):\n243:             for log in e.build_log:\n244:                 if 'error' in log:\n245:                     self.logger.error(log['error'])\n246:         raise\n247: ```\n248: \n249: **`get_image_info`**\n250: ```python\n251: def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n252:     \"\"\"Get information about a Docker image.\n253:     \n254:     Args:\n255:         image_name: Name of the image (with optional tag)\n256:         \n257:     Returns:\n258:         Dict containing:\n259:         - id: Image ID\n260:         - size: Human-readable size\n261:         - created: Creation timestamp\n262:         - tags: List of image tags\n263:         \n264:     Raises:\n265:         docker.errors.ImageNotFound: If image doesn't exist\n266:     \"\"\"\n267:     try:\n268:         image = self.client.images.get(image_name)\n269:         return self._get_image_info(image_name)\n270:     except docker.errors.ImageNotFound:\n271:         self.logger.warning(f\"Image not found: {image_name}\")\n272:         raise\n273: ```\n274: \n275: **`_get_image_info` (internal)**\n276: ```python\n277: def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n278:     \"\"\"Internal method to extract image information.\n279:     \n280:     Args:\n281:         image_name: Name of the image\n282:         \n283:     Returns:\n284:         Dict with image details\n285:     \"\"\"\n286:     image = self.client.images.get(image_name)\n287:     \n288:     # Extract size from image attrs\n289:     size_bytes = image.attrs.get('Size', 0)\n290:     \n291:     return {\n292:         \"id\": image.id,\n293:         \"size\": self._format_size(size_bytes),\n294:         \"created\": image.attrs.get('Created', 'unknown'),\n295:         \"tags\": image.tags,\n296:     }\n297: ```\n298: \n299: **`_format_size` (internal)**\n300: ```python\n301: def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str:\n302:     \"\"\"Format byte size to human-readable string.\n303:     \n304:     Args:\n305:         size_bytes: Size in bytes\n306:         \n307:     Returns:\n308:         Human-readable size (e.g., \"125.5 MB\")\n309:     \"\"\"\n310:     for unit in ['B', 'KB', 'MB', 'GB', 'TB']:\n311:         if size_bytes < 1024.0:\n312:             return f\"{size_bytes:.1f} {unit}\"\n313:         size_bytes /= 1024.0\n314:     return f\"{size_bytes:.1f} PB\"\n315: ```\n316: \n317: **`push_image`**\n318: ```python\n319: def push_image(\n320:     self,\n321:     image_name: str,\n322:     registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n323:     username: Optional[str] = None,\n324:     password: Optional[str] = None,\n325: ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n326:     \"\"\"Push a Docker image to a registry.\n327:     \n328:     Args:\n329:         image_name: Name of the local image\n330:         registry_url: Target registry URL (e.g., \"registry.example.com\")\n331:         username: Registry username (optional)\n332:         password: Registry password (optional)\n333:         \n334:     Returns:\n335:         Dict containing:\n336:         - pushed_image: Full image name in registry\n337:         - push_time: ISO format timestamp\n338:         - registry: Registry URL used\n339:         \n340:     Raises:\n341:         RuntimeError: If push fails\n342:         docker.errors.APIError: If Docker API returns error\n343:     \"\"\"\n344:     if not self.check_docker_available():\n345:         raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n346:     \n347:     self.logger.info(f\"Pushing image: {image_name}\")\n348:     \n349:     # Login if credentials provided\n350:     if username and password and registry_url:\n351:         self._docker_login_sdk(registry_url, username, password)\n352:     \n353:     # Determine target image name\n354:     if registry_url:\n355:         # Tag for target registry\n356:         target_image = f\"{registry_url.rstrip('/')}/{image_name}\"\n357:         self._tag_image_sdk(image_name, target_image)\n358:     else:\n359:         target_image = image_name\n360:     \n361:     start_time = datetime.now()\n362:     \n363:     try:\n364:         # Push with streaming logs\n365:         push_logs = self.client.images.push(target_image, stream=True, decode=True)\n366:         \n367:         if self.verbose:\n368:             for log_line in push_logs:\n369:                 if 'status' in log_line:\n370:                     self.logger.debug(log_line['status'])\n371:                 if 'error' in log_line:\n372:                     raise RuntimeError(f\"Push failed: {log_line['error']}\")\n373:         \n374:         push_time = (datetime.now() - start_time).total_seconds()\n375:         \n376:         self.logger.info(f\"Successfully pushed {target_image} in {push_time:.2f}s\")\n377:         \n378:         return {\n379:             \"pushed_image\": target_image,\n380:             \"push_time\": datetime.now().isoformat(),\n381:             \"registry\": registry_url or \"docker.io\",\n382:         }\n383:         \n384:     except Exception as e:\n385:         self.logger.error(f\"Push failed: {e}\")\n386:         raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to push image: {e}\")\n387: ```\n388: \n389: **`_docker_login_sdk` (internal)**\n390: ```python\n391: def _docker_login_sdk(\n392:     self,\n393:     registry: Optional[str],\n394:     username: str,\n395:     password: str,\n396: ) -> None:\n397:     \"\"\"Login to Docker registry using SDK.\n398:     \n399:     Args:\n400:         registry: Registry URL (None for Docker Hub)\n401:         username: Registry username\n402:         password: Registry password\n403:     \"\"\"\n404:     self.logger.debug(f\"Logging in to registry: {registry or 'docker.io'}\")\n405:     \n406:     try:\n407:         self.client.login(\n408:             username=username,\n409:             password=password,\n410:             registry=registry,\n411:         )\n412:         self.logger.debug(\"Login successful\")\n413:     except docker.errors.APIError as e:\n414:         self.logger.error(f\"Login failed: {e}\")\n415:         raise\n416: ```\n417: \n418: **`_tag_image_sdk` (internal)**\n419: ```python\n420: def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None:\n421:     \"\"\"Tag an image for a different registry/repository.\n422:     \n423:     Args:\n424:         source_image: Original image name\n425:         target_image: Target image name\n426:     \"\"\"\n427:     self.logger.debug(f\"Tagging {source_image} as {target_image}\")\n428:     \n429:     image = self.client.images.get(source_image)\n430:     \n431:     # Parse target image for repo:tag format\n432:     if ':' in target_image:\n433:         repo, tag = target_image.rsplit(':', 1)\n434:     else:\n435:         repo, tag = target_image, \"latest\"\n436:     \n437:     image.tag(repository=repo, tag=tag)\n438:     self.logger.debug(f\"Tagged successfully\")\n439: ```\n440: \n441: **`remove_image`**\n442: ```python\n443: def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool:\n444:     \"\"\"Remove a Docker image.\n445:     \n446:     Args:\n447:         image_name: Name of the image to remove\n448:         \n449:     Returns:\n450:         True if removal succeeded, False otherwise\n451:         \n452:     Note:\n453:         This method is non-blocking - failures are logged as warnings\n454:         but not raised as exceptions.\n455:     \"\"\"\n456:     self.logger.info(f\"Removing image: {image_name}\")\n457:     \n458:     try:\n459:         self.client.images.remove(image_name, force=False, noprune=False)\n460:         self.logger.info(f\"Successfully removed {image_name}\")\n461:         return True\n462:         \n463:     except docker.errors.ImageNotFound:\n464:         self.logger.warning(f\"Image not found (may already be removed): {image_name}\")\n465:         return True  # Consider it success if already gone\n466:         \n467:     except docker.errors.APIError as e:\n468:         self.logger.warning(f\"Failed to remove image {image_name}: {e}\")\n469:         return False\n470: ```\n471: \n472: ---\n473: \n474: ### 2. BuildRuntime Integration\n475: \n476: The `BuildRuntime` uses `DockerService` for local image builds:\n477: \n478: ```python\n479: class BuildRuntime:\n480:     \"\"\"Runtime class responsible for building agent images.\"\"\"\n481:     \n482:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n483:         self.verbose = verbose\n484:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__)\n485:         self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n486:     \n487:     def _build_local(\n488:         self,\n489:         workspace_path: Path,\n490:         metadata: AgentMetadata,\n491:         options: Dict[str, Any],\n492:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n493:         \"\"\"Build image locally using Docker.\"\"\"\n494:         # Validate Docker is available\n495:         if not self.docker_service.check_docker_available():\n496:             raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n497:         \n498:         # Get Dockerfile path\n499:         dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n500:         if not dockerfile_path.exists():\n501:             raise ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found. Run 'pack' first.\")\n502:         \n503:         # Prepare build arguments\n504:         build_args = {}\n505:         if options.get(\"proxy\"):\n506:             build_args[\"HTTP_PROXY\"] = options[\"proxy\"]\n507:             build_args[\"HTTPS_PROXY\"] = options[\"proxy\"]\n508:         \n509:         # Determine image name\n510:         image_name = metadata.agent_name\n511:         tag = metadata.version or \"latest\"\n512:         \n513:         # Build the image\n514:         build_result = self.docker_service.build_image(\n515:             dockerfile_path=dockerfile_path,\n516:             context_path=workspace_path,\n517:             image_name=image_name,\n518:             tag=tag,\n519:             build_args=build_args,\n520:         )\n521:         \n522:         return build_result\n523: ```\n524: \n525: ---\n526: \n527: ### 3. PublishRuntime Integration\n528: \n529: The `PublishRuntime` uses `DockerService` for image preparation:\n530: \n531: ```python\n532: class PublishRuntime:\n533:     \"\"\"Runtime class responsible for publishing agents.\"\"\"\n534:     \n535:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n536:         self.verbose = verbose\n537:         self.provider = provider\n538:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__)\n539:         self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n540:     \n541:     def _prepare_local_image(\n542:         self,\n543:         workspace_path: Path,\n544:         metadata: AgentMetadata,\n545:         options: Dict[str, Any],\n546:     ) -> str:\n547:         \"\"\"Prepare local image for publishing.\"\"\"\n548:         image_name = metadata.agent_name\n549:         \n550:         # Get image info to verify it exists\n551:         try:\n552:             info = self.docker_service.get_image_info(image_name)\n553:             self.logger.info(f\"Found local image: {info['id']}\")\n554:         except docker.errors.ImageNotFound:\n555:             raise ValueError(\n556:                 f\"Image {image_name} not found. Run 'build' first.\"\n557:             )\n558:         \n559:         # Push to registry if credentials provided\n560:         if options.get(\"image_url\"):\n561:             push_result = self.docker_service.push_image(\n562:                 image_name=image_name,\n563:                 registry_url=options.get(\"image_url\"),\n564:                 username=options.get(\"image_username\"),\n565:                 password=options.get(\"image_password\"),\n566:             )\n567:             return push_result[\"pushed_image\"]\n568:         \n569:         return image_name\n570: ```\n571: \n572: ---\n573: \n574: ## Data Models\n575: \n576: ### Build Result Schema\n577: \n578: ```python\n579: {\n580:     \"image_name\": str,       # Full image name with tag (e.g., \"my-agent:v1.0.0\")\n581:     \"image_id\": str,         # Docker image ID (e.g., \"sha256:abc123...\")\n582:     \"image_size\": str,       # Human-readable size (e.g., \"125.5 MB\")\n583:     \"build_time\": str,       # Duration string (e.g., \"15.3s\")\n584: }\n585: ```\n586: \n587: ### Push Result Schema\n588: \n589: ```python\n590: {\n591:     \"pushed_image\": str,     # Full image name in registry\n592:     \"push_time\": str,        # ISO 8601 timestamp\n593:     \"registry\": str,         # Registry URL used\n594: }\n595: ```\n596: \n597: ### Image Info Schema\n598: \n599: ```python\n600: {\n601:     \"id\": str,               # Docker image ID\n602:     \"size\": str,             # Human-readable size\n603:     \"created\": str,          # Creation timestamp\n604:     \"tags\": List[str],       # List of image tags\n605: }\n606: ```\n607: \n608: ---\n609: \n610: ## Error Handling\n611: \n612: ### Error Types\n613: \n614: | Error | Exception | Description |\n615: |-------|-----------|-------------|\n616: | Docker Unavailable | `RuntimeError` | Docker daemon not accessible |\n617: | Build Failed | `docker.errors.BuildError` | Image build failure |\n618: | Image Not Found | `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` | Image doesn't exist |\n619: | Push Failed | `RuntimeError` | Registry push failure |\n620: | API Error | `docker.errors.APIError` | Docker API error |\n621: | Login Failed | `docker.errors.APIError` | Registry authentication failure |\n622: \n623: ### Error Patterns\n624: \n625: **Docker Availability Check:**\n626: ```python\n627: if not self.docker_service.check_docker_available():\n628:     raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n629: ```\n630: \n631: **Build Error Handling:**\n632: ```python\n633: try:\n634:     result = self.docker_service.build_image(...)\n635: except docker.errors.BuildError as e:\n636:     # Log build output for debugging\n637:     if self.verbose:\n638:         for log in e.build_log:\n639:             if 'error' in log:\n640:                 self.logger.error(log['error'])\n641:     raise RuntimeError(f\"Build failed: {e}\")\n642: ```\n643: \n644: **Image Not Found:**\n645: ```python\n646: try:\n647:     info = self.docker_service.get_image_info(image_name)\n648: except docker.errors.ImageNotFound:\n649:     raise ValueError(f\"Image {image_name} not found. Run 'build' first.\")\n650: ```\n651: \n652: **Non-blocking Removal:**\n653: ```python\n654: # remove_image returns bool, doesn't raise\n655: success = self.docker_service.remove_image(image_name)\n656: if not success:\n657:     self.logger.warning(f\"Could not remove image {image_name}\")\n658: ```\n659: \n660: ---\n661: \n662: ## Configuration\n663: \n664: ### Environment Variables\n665: \n666: | Variable | Used For |\n667: |----------|----------|\n668: | `DOCKER_HOST` | Docker daemon socket/address |\n669: | `DOCKER_TLS_VERIFY` | Enable TLS verification |\n670: | `DOCKER_CERT_PATH` | Path to TLS certificates |\n671: | `HTTP_PROXY` / `HTTPS_PROXY` | Proxy for registry operations |\n672: | `NO_PROXY` | Comma-separated list of hosts to bypass proxy |\n673: \n674: ### Docker Client Configuration\n675: \n676: The Docker client is initialized lazily using `docker.from_env()` which reads:\n677: - Environment variables (DOCKER_HOST, etc.)\n678: - Docker config file (~/.docker/config.json)\n679: - System defaults\n680: \n681: ---\n682: \n683: ## Testing Strategy\n684: \n685: ### Unit Tests\n686: \n687: 1. **DockerService tests**:\n688:    - `test_check_docker_available_success` - Docker daemon accessible\n689:    - `test_check_docker_available_failure` - Docker daemon unavailable\n690:    - `test_build_image_success` - Successful image build\n691:    - `test_build_image_failure` - Build error handling\n692:    - `test_get_image_info` - Image inspection\n693:    - `test_format_size` - Size formatting for various byte values\n694:    - `test_push_image_success` - Successful push\n695:    - `test_push_image_with_auth` - Push with credentials\n696:    - `test_remove_image_success` - Successful removal\n697:    - `test_remove_image_not_found` - Non-existent image handling\n698: \n699: 2. **Integration with Runtime tests**:\n700:    - `test_build_local_uses_docker_service` - BuildRuntime integration\n701:    - `test_publish_prepares_image` - PublishRuntime integration\n702: \n703: ### Mock Strategy\n704: \n705: ```python\n706: # Mock Docker client for unit tests\n707: @pytest.fixture\n708: def mock_docker_client():\n709:     with patch('docker.from_env') as mock_from_env:\n710:         client = MagicMock()\n711:         mock_from_env.return_value = client\n712:         yield client\n713: \n714: def test_build_image_success(mock_docker_client):\n715:     # Setup mock\n716:     mock_image = MagicMock()\n717:     mock_image.id = \"sha256:abc123\"\n718:     mock_image.attrs = {'Size': 131072000}\n719:     mock_image.tags = [\"test:latest\"]\n720:     \n721:     mock_docker_client.images.build.return_value = (\n722:         mock_image,\n723:         [{'stream': 'Step 1/5'}, {'stream': 'Successfully built'}]\n724:     )\n725:     mock_docker_client.images.get.return_value = mock_image\n726:     \n727:     # Test\n728:     service = DockerService(verbose=False)\n729:     result = service.build_image(\n730:         dockerfile_path=Path(\"Dockerfile\"),\n731:         context_path=Path(\".\"),\n732:         image_name=\"test\",\n733:         tag=\"latest\",\n734:     )\n735:     \n736:     # Assert\n737:     assert result[\"image_name\"] == \"test:latest\"\n738:     assert result[\"image_size\"] == \"125.0 MB\"\n739: ```\n740: \n741: ### Integration Tests\n742: \n743: 1. **Docker Operations E2E**:\n744:    - Build simple Python agent image\n745:    - Push to local registry (if available)\n746:    - Verify image info retrieval\n747:    - Cleanup/remove image\n748: \n749: 2. **Error Scenarios**:\n750:    - Docker daemon not running\n751:    - Invalid Dockerfile syntax\n752:    - Registry authentication failure\n753:    - Network timeout during push\n754: \n755: ---\n756: \n757: ## Security Considerations\n758: \n759: 1. **Registry Credentials**:\n760:    - Credentials passed via parameters, never logged\n761:    - Docker SDK handles credential storage securely\n762:    - Support for credential helpers (~/.docker/config.json)\n763: \n764: 2. **Image Security**:\n765:    - Build context is limited to workspace directory\n766:    - No sensitive files should be in build context\n767:    - .dockerignore support for excluding files\n768: \n769: 3. **Network Security**:\n770:    - HTTPS for registry operations\n771:    - TLS verification for Docker daemon\n772:    - Proxy support for corporate environments\n773: \n774: 4. **Resource Limits**:\n775:    - Consider memory limits for build operations\n776:    - Build timeout handling\n777:    - Concurrent build limitations\n778: \n779: ---\n780: \n781: ## Performance Characteristics\n782: \n783: | Operation | Typical Duration | Notes |\n784: |-----------|------------------|-------|\n785: | Docker availability check | <100ms | Ping operation |\n786: | Image build | 10s - 5min | Depends on image size and layers |\n787: | Image info retrieval | <100ms | Local Docker operation |\n788: | Image push | 10s - 5min | Depends on image size and network |\n789: | Image removal | <1s | Local operation |\n790: \n791: ### Optimization Strategies\n792: \n793: 1. **Layer Caching**: Leverage Docker layer caching for faster rebuilds\n794: 2. **Parallel Operations**: Build/push operations can be parallelized\n795: 3. **Progress Streaming**: Stream logs for better UX on long operations\n796: 4. **Image Pruning**: Cleanup intermediate images to save disk space\n797: \n798: ---\n799: \n800: ## Dependencies\n801: \n802: ### External Dependencies\n803: \n804: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n805: |---------|---------|---------|\n806: | `docker` | >=6.0.0 | Docker SDK for Python |\n807: | `requests` | >=2.25.0 | HTTP library (Docker SDK dependency) |\n808: | `urllib3` | >=1.26.0 | HTTP client (Docker SDK dependency) |\n809: \n810: ### Python Requirements\n811: \n812: ```toml\n813: [project]\n814: dependencies = [\n815:     \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n816:     # ... other deps\n817: ]\n818: ```\n819: \n820: ---\n821: \n822: ## Future Enhancements\n823: \n824: 1. **BuildKit Support**: Use BuildKit for advanced build features\n825: 2. **Multi-platform Builds**: Support for cross-platform image builds\n826: 3. **Build Cache Export**: Export/import build cache for CI/CD\n827: 4. **Image Scanning**: Integration with vulnerability scanners\n828: 5. **Parallel Builds**: Build multiple images concurrently\n829: 6. **Build Metrics**: Detailed timing and resource usage metrics\n830: \n831: ---\n832: \n833: ## References\n834: \n835: - [cli-toolkit/design.md](../../cli-toolkit/design.md) - Overall CLI design\n836: - [cli-toolkit/spec.md](../../cli-toolkit/spec.md) - CLI specification\n837: - [Docker SDK for Python](https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/) - Official SDK docs\n838: - [Docker Engine API](https://docs.docker.com/engine/api/) - REST API reference\n\n(End of file - total 838 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024: DockerService Encapsulation — Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document provides technical implementation details for the `DockerService` component in the AgentCube CLI project. The DockerService provides a high-level abstraction over the Docker SDK for building, managing, and publishing container images.\n\n**AR:** AR-024  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                            CLI Layer                                          │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md","time":{"start":1775897150259,"end":1775897150270}}}}
